title: rich spice cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, shortening and egg yolks.
Combine flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, nutmeg and baking soda mixing with egg yolk mixture alternately with sour milk.
Fold stiff egg whites and raisins into mixture.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Grind beef up real fine and cook in skillet.
After rice is done, mix ground beef in rice and stir good.
Scramble 6 eggs real fine and stir into rice and beef mixture.
Serve with red kidney beans (heated) or can be added to the wild rice, beef and egg mixture.
Can also season with garlic, onion or other seasonings desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: quick and zesty vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until noodles are done.
Makes 8 servings (1 cup each).
Frozen vegetables may be substituted for canned, but add 2 cups more of the broth.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Combine buttermilk with soda.
Mix flour, sugar and salt. Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour, etc., and mix well.
Continue to beat as you add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk with soda.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° for 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.

title: clear sauce
directions: Bring water to a boil; add butter.
Then stir in sugar and cornstarch, mixed smooth in a little cold water.
Stir the sauce constantly while it cooks until clear.
Then remove from heat and add vanilla flavoring.
Serve hot over puddings, date and nut cake or Poor Man's Cake.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend eggs, milk and butter.
Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Mix corn, onions, garlic, shallots and cheese.
Add flour mixture to corn mixture.
Add egg mixture and stir.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's fudge pudding surprise
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, and salt. Stir in milk and oil.
Add nuts.
Pour thick batter into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Chill for 3 hours.
Roll in powdered sugar before serving.
May be frozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Thin down the soups with 1 1/2 cups of chicken stock and season to taste with salt and pepper. Optional thyme and extra chopped green chili to taste. Bring to simmer in a large saucepan over medium heat and stir occasionally.

title: grilled chicken with dijon sauce
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice and dill weed.
Lightly brush chicken with oil and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place under broiler or over medium-hot coals, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Brush sauce on one side of meat before removing from broiler.

title: mom's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake until done (325° for 40 minutes).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all veggies well with cream cheese.
Fold in drained shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: greek crescent cookies
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup powdered sugar, the egg yolk, ouzo and almond extract.
Stir in flour.
Shape dough by teaspoonfuls into crescent shapes.
Place about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light brown on bottom (12 to 15 minutes).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.
Cool on wire racks.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls on a 17 x 11 cookie pan. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. While hot, spread on cream cheese. Next, mix sour cream with Hidden Valley Ranch dip mix. Spread over cream cheese. Top with your favorite veggies. Add Cheddar cheese and bacon bits. Keep chilled.

title: apple-chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat well. Add water and vanilla.
Combine soda, flour and salt and add to shortening mixture.
Add oatmeal, chips, apples and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Drain all juices and syrups from fruit.
Mix all together and serve cold.

title: quick artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Serve with French bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Cook onions and celery until tender in butter.
Set aside.
In another pan, melt Cheez Whiz, soup and evaporated milk.
When melted, add celery, onions and cooked rice.
Pour over broccoli and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: oven-fried zucchini spears
directions: In Ziploc bag, combine oil and water.
Add zucchini spears and shake to coat.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, garlic salt, paprika and pepper in a dish.
Mix well.
Add zucchini spears and coat with crumb mixture.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or until tender.

title: shortbread
directions: Soften butter, then mix with remaining ingredients until coarse crumbs appear.
Spread out on cookie sheet with sides. Press flat with hands.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Prick with a fork all over.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Cut immediately into small squares or strips.

title: vegetable turkey pockets
directions: Mix dressings, turkey, cucumber, carrot, tomato and basil. Refrigerate.
Fill bread with turkey mixture.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: baked macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni until tender, but firm; drain.
Put in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter (in microwave) and coat bread crumbs; set aside.

title: diet popsicles
directions: Mix in a pitcher, mixture will foam.
Let rest until foam subsides.
Pour into forms until 1/4-inch from tops.
Put into freezer for approximately 3 hours.

title: fresh raspberry omelette
directions: Stem and gently rinse berries.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle sugar over berries; gently toss to mix.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Use an omelette pan or skillet.
Melt butter in pan.
When slightly browned, pour in eggs.
Swirl skillet or pan several times while cooking so uncooked egg will run onto surface of pan.
When mixture begins to thicken but is still soft, remove pan from heat and spoon berries onto half.
Flip other half over to cover berries.
Cover with lid; let stand 5 minutes.
Slide omelette onto a warm plate; top with dollop of sour cream or plain yogurt. Serves 2.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix in order:
Cool Whip, nuts, marshmallows and pineapple. Mix all well.
Last add dry pistachio pudding mix.
Chill overnight.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make a syrup of sugar, vinegar and cinnamon, cooking them together for 20 minutes.
Remove skins of peaches by dipping them for a moment in boiling water, then rubbing with a cloth.
Stick 2 cloves in each peach and then cook in syrup until tender.
Do not try to cook too many peaches at one time.
Boil the syrup 10 minutes after all the fruit is done, then pour it over the peaches and seal.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in casserole dish.
Stir 1/2 can of onions into beans.
Stir in soup and milk.
Place in microwave on High for about 8 minutes.
Add rest of onions to top of beans and continue cooking for about 2 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, mix milk, egg and cooking oil.
Add wet ingredients to dry.
Spray frying pan with Pam and cook pancakes on medium-high heat.
Flip.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in milk.
Add cocoa and bring to slow boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix and spoon onto wax paper.
Let harden at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant thickly.
Dip in flour.
Brown in butter in a large frying pan.
Lay aside on a plate.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Mix onion, green pepper and tomatoes in the frying pan.
(If using fresh tomatoes, a little water may be necessary.) Mix in 1 tablespoon of the flour and season with salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
Fill casserole with alternate layers of this mixture and eggplant.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese to garnish.
Bake a few more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy tomato sauce
directions: Cook onion in oil in a heavy saucepan over moderately low heat, stirring until softened. Add garlic and cook, stirring 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes and puree, sugar and salt and pepper to taste and bring to boil. Simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes. Stir in basil and water.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix and drink 2 ounces once a day.

title: okie's vegetable stew
directions: Combine all vegetables.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients and set aside.
In a microwave-safe bowl, heat chips and oil on medium-high for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Microwave on high for 10 seconds, stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix well.
Spread onto three waxed paper-lined baking sheets.
Cook and break apart.
Store in an airtight container.

title: swiss chocolate squares
directions: Combine water, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 1/2 chocolate squares in saucepan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt and mix well.

title: oven fried chicken and bananas
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces on all sides with salt and pepper. In a bowl, mix cream of coconut and lemon juice.
Peel bananas and cut each into half crosswise.
Brush chicken and bananas thickly with cream of coconut mixture and roll in crumbs, pressing firmly to make them adhere.
Brush a baking pan with some of the butter. Place chicken in single layer in pan and drizzle with half the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add bananas and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: roasted new potatoes and herbs
directions: Combine all except parsley.
Toss to coat potatoes.
Place potatoes in single layer on sheet of heavy-duty foil.
Fold foil over potatoes and crimp edges to seal.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.
Open foil and sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: fishman's wharf cioppino
directions: Salt green peppers and onions; stir-fry in frypan.
Put pork and juice in pan or pot.
Use fresh sauerkraut.
Cook 2 or 3 white potatoes separately.
When done, cut in cubes; mix all together. Let simmer about 30 minutes.
Use other seasonings if you wish.

title: wild turkey supreme
directions: Preheat water smoker or start fire with full pan of charcoal. Pat turkey dry inside and out.
Stuff cavity with onion, parsley and carrots.
Sew and truss.
Place bacon over turkey breast.

title: refrigerator angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine in bowl, flour, soda, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast water to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in half gallon container in refrigerator.
Use as needed for hot rolls.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
This dough is very sticky when it is ready to use.
It doesn't need more flour.
The stickiness is a characteristic of this recipe.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Beat eggs and half and half until blended.
Stir in cheese. Crumble bacon on bottom of pie crust or lay crabmeat . Pour egg, milk and cheese mixture over top.
Mushrooms may be added. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake quiche about 45 to 50 minutes, until pie shell is brown and filling firm.
Let set up about 10 minutes before slicing.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Drain all the liquid from all the cans of fruit. Thin the sour cream with whichever fruit juice you would like. Mix all the ingredients together with the thin sour cream. Chill and serve.

title: grandma lutz noodles
directions: Break eggs in bowl and beat.
Add milk, salt (pepper if you like), baking powder and a little yellow food coloring.
Mix well.
Put flour in large bowl.
Pour egg mixture in middle of flour and mix with fork until sticks together to work by hand (like pizza or pie dough).

title: sour cream spice cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve soda and sour cream.
Add alternately with remaining ingredients. Drop on greased tin.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers

title: south carolina cookies
directions: In saucepan, add margarine, sugar, dates, salt and eggs. Bring to full boil and cook for 6 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, rice crispies and pecans.
(Do not substitute pecans.)
Mix well; cool slightly and roll into balls, then roll balls in coconut.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and onions (or bell peppers).
Spread ham slices with mixture.
Slice in 1/2 to 3/4 inch slices after rolling.
Serve with your favorite cracker.

title: old fashioned sour cream cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat at medium speed, the butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until light.
At low speed, beat in sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stove top chicken casserole
directions: Break chicken into pieces.
Place in casserole.
Cover with sour cream-soup mixture and celery.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing (as directed on package); place on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gram's blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix until blended.
Add dry ingredients, mixing with milk alternately. Wash berries and pat dry.
Sprinkle with a little flour so berries won't sink to bottom of batter.
Fold in berries.
Fill paper lined muffin tins 3/4 full.
Sprinkle sugar on top of muffins.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes about 18.

title: lemon blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with cooking spray.
For topping, combine the 2 tablespoons of oats and 2 tablespoons of sugar in a small bowl;
mix well.
Set aside.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Add flavoring, nuts and morsels.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Reduce heat to 300° and place foil over top of pan and bake 15 more minutes.
Cool on rack in pan 10 to 15 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: I sometimes add a can of vacuum packed corn for extra crunch.

title: boiled fruit cake
directions: Bring raisins to boil in 2 cups water.
Let simmer 10 minutes; let cool and add molasses.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
In large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Add creamed mixture, then add raisins and mix all together.
Put in well-greased pan (greased with Crisco) and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: fresh blueberry jam
directions: Combine the lemon juice, water, gelatin and arrowroot in a saucepan.
Heat until dissolved, then add the blueberries.
Cook, stirring, until thickened, then boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sweetener.
There are 9 calories per tablespoon.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Stir and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: best pizza in town
directions: Dial 644-2070 and order 1 large pepperoni and extra cheese to be delivered.

title: speedy gazpacho soup(makes 6 cups or 8 first course servings.)
directions: Two and half hours before serving, pour into large bowl undiluted tomato soup.
In small saucepan, heat 2 soup cans water to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in bouillon until dissolved. Add broth to tomato soup, stirring until well blended.
Stir in vinegar and next 7 ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, until well chilled.
Serve with corn chips.

title: orange beef
directions: Mix flour and dry ingredients.
Coat meat cubes.
Use any remaining flour as thickening after browning beef.
Add liquids and mushrooms and simmer 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: buffet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool.
Add pineapple and juice.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese; spread on first layer.
Spread lemon pie filling on second layer.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top, if desired.
Keep chilled.

title: jalapeno bread
directions: Mix and cook at 375°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Thinly slice flank steak, diagonally.
Brown with the onion in the oil.
Stir in the mixture of gravy mix, water and soy sauce. Stir until thickened.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add bell peppers, cut in thin strips, and the tomato, cut in wedges.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: coffee chocolate chip waffles
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, yeast, sugar and salt. Stir together.
Whisk together the milk, coffee, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Stir into the dry ingredient mixture, stirring enough to blend.
Cover with plastic wrap and allow to sit in warm place until doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips. Preheat the waffle iron according to manufacturers instructions. Spoon in enough of the batter to cover the iron.
Bake until done and golden brown.

title: our favorite crunchy cookies
directions: Beat sugar, brown sugar, oil, margarine and egg until fluffy. Add baking soda, baking powder, salt and sour milk.
Add flour and vanilla.
Fold in oats, cornflakes, nuts and chocolate chips.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and lemonade.
Spread in crust, then refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey tacos
directions: In a skillet bring the stock to a boil and add the onions and bell pepper.
Saute the vegetables over medium heat until softened (about 5 to 7 minutes).
Add the cilantro, chiles, chicken or turkey, rice and seasonings.
Stir well, cover and cook over low heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Heat the tortillas in the oven until hot but still pliable.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of the filling into each warmed tortilla.
Add raw vegetable garnishes.
Fold tortilla in half and eat sandwich style.
A dollop of nonfat yogurt, a few drops of bottled hot sauce or picante sauce and a little chopped fresh cilantro may be used as additional garnishes for extra flavor.
Yields 12 tacos (about 4 to 6 servings).

title: banana loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, bananas, salt, flour and nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it passes the toothpick test.
This is delicious served with butter, cream cheese or just plain.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in a 3-quart bowl the brown sugar, flour, pumpkin pie spice (see note) and salt. Add and stir until smooth the milk and egg, slightly beaten. Pour into 9-inch crust. Bake in 375° oven 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.

title: rolls (crescent)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, shortening and salt; let cool.
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add flour; don't get dough too stiff.
Turn dough into greased bowl, grease top of dough, then cover with cloth.
Let rise at least 2 hours.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board, about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut 1 inch long. Dip in butter, then twist 2 times.
Lay on greased pan.
Let rise about 20 minutes.
Bake until done.

title: mexican pizzas
directions: Brown meat and drain off grease.
Melt cheese on tortilla shells.
Put sauce on meat.
Add to shells.
Sprinkle on cheese. Add tomatoes and onions to shells.
Put under broiler to melt cheese.

title: fresh fruit bowl
directions: Combine
fruit	in large bowl;	toss gently.
Cover and chill. Serve with Mandarin Dressing.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tuna logs(refrigerated)
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make into two rolls and chill overnight.
Serve as an appetizer with crackers.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix rest of ingredients, except sauce, together in a bowl.
Drain and rinse noodles.
Take a tablespoon of the mixture and put in middle of noodle and roll up.
Do the same for rest of noodles.
Place in a 15 x 10-inch pan and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.
Take cover off last 15 minutes.

title: lazy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an oblong baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk.
Pour this over batter.
Do not stir!
Spoon fruit into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients first, then cut in margarine.
Put 1/2 of mix on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread cranberry sauce, then top with remaining mix.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: cherry top cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured bundt pan at 350° until done (about 30 minutes).
When cake has completely cooled, sift 2 Tbsp powdered sugar over cake.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Fry onion in small amount of butter, then add hamburger.
Cook until slightly brown.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick enough to spoon on bun and serve with slaw.

title: cooked maple syrup
directions: Boil 2 cups water, as it just gets to boiling, add sugars, flavoring and maple syrup.
Bring to a boil again.
Turn heat to medium, let boil at least 5 minutes.
Turn off heat, leave on burner cool and store*.
I store this in the refrigerator in a sterilized canning jar with a lid.

title: peppered steak
directions: Pound steak, then slice into thin strips.
Sprinkle with paprika; let stand 15 minutes.
Melt butter and brown meat.
Add beef bouillon.
Add garlic and green onions.

title: amish shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until crumbs are formed.

title: dip for nachos
directions: Cube Velveeta cheese and put in crock-pot.
Fry sausage; drain and crumble.
Add to cheese, then add soup and evaporated milk.
Heat until hot and bubbly.
Serve with nachos.

title: ham balls - sweet and sour
directions: In a medium sized bowl combine ground meats, crumbs, eggs and pepper.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form into small balls.
Set aside.

title: remschner's reuben casserole
directions: Spread sauerkraut on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Dot with dressing and butter.
Cover with corned beef; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven. Separate each biscuit into three layers; slightly overlap biscuit layers on casserole to form three rows.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until biscuit topping is golden brown.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Blend butter, cream cheese, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add sugar and enough powdered milk to form a stiff ball.
Make into egg shapes and coat with chocolate or chopped nuts or both.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides.
Seal perforations. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely. Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper until smooth. Spread evenly over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into appetizer-size pieces.
Store in refrigerator.

title: rolled gingerbread cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and chill 3 hours.
Roll into 2 inch balls, then roll them in sugar and crisscross with a fork to flatten. Bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Place chicken, garlic, onions, broth and 2 cups of wine in large pot on top of stove.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat to simmer.
Simmer until chicken is falling from bones.
Remove chicken from pot and pull meat from bones.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oats,
brown sugar, butter and cinnamon. Mix until crumbly. Press
half	of
mixture
into
9-inch pan. Cover with rhubarb.
Cook
white	sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla until thickened and
clear.
Pour
over
rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.	Top with Cool Whip.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Beat sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, for 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl, occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk on low speed.
Pour into pan.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat with olive oil, onion and garlic.
Stir in chili powder, paprika, oregano, salt, pepper, tomatoes and water. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Marinate all ingredients overnight.

title: quick quiche
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch in blender.
Stir in meat, cheese, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: turtle cake
directions: Day 1:
Put starter in a 1-gallon container and add 2 1/2 cups sugar and a 16-ounce can sliced peaches with juice.
Stir together, cover and let stand at room temperature.
(Do not refrigerate!!!)
Stir everyday.
Fruit may bubble up and the top pop off.
This is normal.
Keep covered.

title: quick punch
directions: Put ingredients (chilled) in a large punch bowl.
An ice ring of 7-up can be added if desired.
Gently mix and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together all except wax and chips and roll into balls.
Dip into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper to cool.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; saute onion.
Combine with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Spoon enough meat mixture and cheese on each tortilla to cover a third of it.
Roll tortilla, beginning at the filled edge.
Place, seam side down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When tortillas are completed, combine soup, sour cream and green chiles to make a sauce; pour over tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle reserved cheese over top.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange and onion salad
directions: Layer oranges and onion.
Stir all other ingredients together. Mix well and dribble over layers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place 1/2 of the potatoes and onions in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 1/2 of the butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the dry ingredients over potatoes.
Layer remaining potatoes and onions; top with the remaining dry ingredients.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and continue to bake until done and brown (about 45 minutes).
For variety, melt some cheese on top.

title: turkey cashew cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly sprinkle pepper over cutlets. Place a cheese slice on each
cutlet.
Roll-up
cutlet jelly-roll style to encase cheese.
Carefully coat each cutlet;
roll in bread crumbs.
In a 14 oz. oval casserole dish, arrange cutlet rolls, seam-side down.
Spoon Worcestershire sauce over cutlets. Bake 10 minutes.
Baste cutlets with pan drippings.
Sprinkle cashews over top.
Bake 5 minutes, or until turkey is no longer pink in center.
Yields: 2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown the hamburg and the onion.
Mix the soup and the milk together so there is enough to cover the potatoes.
Layer all the ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake 2 hours at 325° to 350°.
The last 5 to 10 minutes, add a can of Durkee onions.
Brown slightly.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Measure the first 7 ingredients into a mixing bowl; blend by hand or mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in the baking powder.
Add the milk, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into pans greased with Crisco and lined with waxed paper.
Bake round layers for 25 to 30 minutes, square pans for 30 to 35 minutes and cupcakes for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk in a large saucepan.
When candy starts to boil, boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter chips, vanilla and butter.
When set firm, cut into desired size pieces.
Makes 6 pounds candy.

title: old fashioned bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Place all ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix by hand.
Pour mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Stir in sherbet until melted.
Drain mandarin oranges well and cut slices in several pieces.
Add to jello mix.
Pour into a pretty mold and chill to set.

title: baby plum cake
directions: Add all ingredients in the order listed: sugar, oil, eggs, flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, plum baby food and chopped nuts until well mixed.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Cook at 300° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 20 minutes.

title: japanese fruitcake pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients to eggs.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: italian style rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine water, rice and salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: liver and onions
directions: Pound liver to make tender; salt.
Batter with flour.
Brown quickly on both sides in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Slice onion crosswise.
Scatter over top of liver. Cover liver with water.
Cover and simmer until tender and gravy is thick.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Place crackers in 1 gallon freezer bag.
Use hands or rolling pin to crush into crumbs.
Drain cherry juice and save. Combine all ingredients but cherry juice and mix in an extra large bowl. Mix with mixer until well blended.
Add juice slowly, only enough to make ingredients stick together.
Chill 1 hour.
Separate into 4 equal parts and roll into logs.
Wrap each in wax paper to keep fresh.
Decorate with cherries and pecans.

title: poor boy casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan.
Add bell peppers and onions (chopped) to bacon fat.
Let simmer until done but not brown.
To this, add tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until juice is almost gone.
Break up toast and bacon into tomato mixture.
Place in a casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese vegetable sandwich mix
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise together until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Let set 1/2 hour to blend together.
Serve on crackers or as a sandwich filling.

title: zippy cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Yields 1 cup.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in top of double boiler. Beat egg yolks and milk together; add to sugar mixture. Cook until thickened. Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made with the egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix both packages Jello with hot water, dissolve completely. Add blueberries and pineapple (juice included).
Refrigerate until set.
Using electric mixer, mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Spread this on top of congealed mixture. May top with chopped pecans if desired.

title: gingered sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour in 425° oven.
Scoop out potato flesh and food process until pureed.
In large mixer bowl, place puree, sugar, eggs, 4 tablespoons of butter, orange rind, ground ginger, salt, pepper and crystallized ginger.
Blend well and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Drain shrimp and flake; add margarine, onion and lemon juice; mix.
Add additional ingredients.
Press into decorative mold or other container.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: beer bisquits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix beer, sugar and bisquick. Fill muffin pan about 1/2 full no more. Bake until golden brown.

title: easy as pie cheese straws
directions: Mix in food processor.
Process about 30 seconds or until it forms a ball.
Use cookie press for straws or may divide in half and shape each into a 7-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 1 hour.
Slice and place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In large saucepan, put potatoes, broth, carrots, onions, parsley, celery seed, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make 1 yellow cake mix as directed (sheet style).
Mix pudding with milk.
Add cream cheese.
Top cake with pudding and cheese. Mix pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Decorate with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture and set aside for top.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Cook milk, sugar and butter, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes on low temperature.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream and Kisses.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in chopped pecans.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except peaches.
Pour into an 8 x 11-inch ovenproof shallow dish.
Top with peaches and bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
(Cobbler will still be slightly runny.)
Let set 15 minutes and serve warm.

title: frostin the snowman eggnog
directions: Blend eggs and sugar; add milk and chill!
Fold in whipping cream and vanilla.
Add all together.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolk.
Add mashed bananas. Add flour alternately with milk. Add stiffly beaten egg whites. Mix well. Bake in moderate oven 1 hour.

title: horseradish gravy
directions: Strain broth through fine sieve.
Measure 3 cups.
Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add to stock.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and thickened.
Stir in sour cream slowly.
Add horseradish.
Makes 4 cups.
Serve warm.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directions on box.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar (cheese must be room temperature).
Mix the cheese mixture with the Dream Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top. Chill.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse.
Layer meat sauce, cheese and noodles, having cheese on final layer. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add 3 egg yolks and 2 whole eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Then fold in with spoon the 3 egg whites. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture. Chill.
Roll out.
Cut with various cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: schneiboin soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook all day on low.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Microwave on High 1 minute and 45 seconds first 2 ingredients. Stir with rubber spatula. Microwave 1 minute longer.
Stir in 1 jar of peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: georgie's salad dressing
directions: Mix and serve with green salad.
Makes 2 servings.
Can easily be enlarged.
Leave
out Mrs. Dash and substitute poppy seeds for mustard green salads.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook
chicken
and debone.
Cut into bite-sized pieces. Cook rice
according
to package.
Saute onions in margarine. Dissolve flour in milk.
Add milk/flour mixture to onions; add both cans of
soup.
Blend
over
low
heat until thick sauce forms.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
In a large casserole dish,
layer sauce,
rice,
chicken
and cheese.
Layer again ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until bubbly).
Serves 12 to 14.

title: chicken picante(quick and easy)
directions: Place one cup picante sauce into a large saucepan.
Add chicken breasts to picante sauce and bring to a bubbling boil. Lower heat and continue gently boil for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink inside.
Serves 2.

title: mexican pie
directions: Press crescent rolls in pie pan and bake until golden brown. Mix and set aside mayonnaise, sour cream and 1/2 cup onion.
Pepper and garlic to taste.
Layer as follows in shell crust:
hamburg, ripe olives, tomatoes, half of Cheddar cheese, sour cream/mayonnaise mixture and then remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in hot water.
Add bananas, pineapple, strawberries and nuts. Mix well and pour 1/2 of the mixture into salad dish. Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on top and pour rest of the mixture on top of the sour cream. Chill to set.

title: beads
directions: Dissolve salt in heated water; stir in cornstarch and food coloring (optional).
Knead until smooth.
Pinch off small amounts; form into shapes.
Stick small dowels or pencils through them and place on waxed paper.
When beads are dry, slip off sticks and thread onto yarn.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Dump the whole mess in a blender and whirl it 2 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together the first twelve ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Cook noodles.

title: chicken salad(100 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add eggs, celery, salt, pepper, pickles and mayonnaise to chicken; mix well.
Serve immediately, or cover with waxed paper and store in the refrigerator.
Makes 100 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: fried turkey
directions: Note:
Less ingredients and oil for fryer or turkey breast.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except Corn Chex and margarine.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crush Corn Chex cereal and pat on top. Melt margarine, pour onto Chex.
Bake at 400° 45-60 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, salt, butter and boiling water.
When warm, not hot, add yeast.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour into yeast mixture, egg and rest of flour.
Sprinkle board with small amount of flour and work dough into ball.
Grease mixing bowl.
Put dough in bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double in size.
Work down and make into rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: marinated roasted pepper roll-ups
directions: Place peppers on towel and pat dry.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Then combine parsley and green onions. Spread very thin layer of cheese mixture on tortilla.
Then layer with roasted peppers.
Wrap up like jelly roll.
Wrap up roll in plastic wrap for about 2 hours in fridge.
Unwrap, slice and serve. Time Saver Alternative:
Substitute cream cheese, sour cream and mayo for (onion/chive Weis brand cream cheese).

title: nun's puffs
directions: Heat to a boil milk and butter.
Add flour all at one time and beat with an electric mixer.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each egg.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins, 1/2 to 2/3 full. Sprinkle with sugar and bake.
No peeking!

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Melt together margarine, water and peanut butter.
Mix flour, soda, sugar, salt, sour milk, vanilla and eggs into mixture.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: christmas doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Beat eggs, whipping cream, vanilla and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir into yeast.
Stir in remaining ingredients except oil until dough is soft and easy to handle.

title: lime pickles
directions: Combine
cucumbers, water and lime.
Soak for 24 hours; stir occasionally,
drain and wash well.
Soak for 3 hours in ice water, stir often.
Drain.
Mix together other ingredients with cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Heat to boiling point and boil for 35 minutes; then can.

title: la compe lemon pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch. Add enough milk to wet dry ingredients. Beat in egg yolks; blend well. Add remainder of milk and butter. Cook to custard consistency over a low fire.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice and grated lemon peel.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until they are light and hold a peak.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar, one at a time, beating after each addition. Spread on pie and brown slowly.

title: oatmeal toll house cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add eggs.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Sprinkle
a little flour over nuts and chocolate bits. Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: kahlua fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, stir oleo, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients until well mixed. Pour into sprayed pie tins and cool at room temperature.

title: eleanore alborano's sugar-free apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts according to box.
Cut apples.
Place in pie shell as they are cut.
Put a packet of Equal and a teaspoon of nutmeg and cinnamon for each layer.
Continue to layer the rest of the apples and seasoning.
After sealing the pie, brush the top crust lightly with milk.
Sprinkle a packet of Equal on the top. Preheat oven. Bake at 375° (electric oven for 15 minutes). Bake the pie at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool briefly. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or Cheddar cheese.

title: chicken-cheese ball
directions: Mix chicken, dry salad mix and cream cheese.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Shape into balls.
Roll in pecans.
Cover and chill.

title: carolina cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pepper and onion.
Bring sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt, celery seed and oil to a boil.
Pour over slaw mixture.
Cool; cover and refrigerate.
Gets better with age. Serve over Coney Island Hot Dog or barbecue sandwiches.

title: fruity slush
directions: Bring sugar and 3 cups of water to a boil, stirring often. Remove from heat.

title: ginger-peachy-mandarin punch
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill, serve in a tall glass over crushed ice.
If adding vodka, add right before serving.
Serves 1.

title: chocolate macaroon cake
directions: Beat 1 egg white with 1 tsp. vanilla until soft mounds form. Add 1/2 cup sugar, beat until stiff.
Stir in coconut and 1 Tbsp. flour, set aside.
Beat remaining egg whites until soft mounds form, then add 1/2 cup sugar gradually, beating until meringue stands in stiff peaks.
Set aside also.
Add soda to sour cream and stir well.
Cream remaining sugar and shortening, add egg yolks, salt, vanilla and half the coffee mixture.
Beat 4 minutes, or until light and creamy.
Add flour, sour cream mixture and remaining coffee mixture, blend well, then fold in egg whites. Grease bottom of 10 inch tube pan and pour 1/3 of cake batter into it.
Gently spoon half the coconut mixture on top, cover with half the remaining chocolate batter, rest of coconut mixture and rest of chocolate batter.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees, bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cook completely before removing from pan, then frost cake.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook in large pot the chicken, covered with water.
Add poultry season, salt and pepper.
If desired, add onions, celery leaves and carrots.
When tender, remove chicken from bone and cut into pieces.
Set aside.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Let set for several hours.

title: allen's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Lightly spoon flour
into
measuring cup and level off. In a large bowl
combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With fork or
pastry blender, cut margarine into mixture until consistency of coarse meal.
Store in tightly covered container and refrigerate or freeze.
Use within 4 weeks.
Measure by dipping cup into
mixture.
Return unused amount to refrigerator or freezer.
Allow
measured
mix to come to room temperature before adding ingredients.

title: brownies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa. Add butter, egg and vanilla; mix well. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. You can use a 9 x 9 for thick brownies or 13 x 9 for thinner brownies.

title: bean casserole
directions: In a medium sized sauce pan, brown the hamburger along with the onion.
Drain.
Add the pintos, kidney and butter (or lima) beans.
Stir.
Add chili powder, vinegar, brown sugar and ketchup. Throw in a dash of salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Stir once more before serving.
Enjoy!

title: adam's bmw
directions: Stir and enjoy!
Nice during summer or any time!

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water, pineapple juice, salt and green pepper strips.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with cold water.
Add this to hot mixture.
Cook until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Then add pineapple chunks, cherries and paprika.
Add chicken or pork.

title: linda's honey wheat bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together, then add oatmeal and whole-wheat flour. Mix thoroughly. Then add the white flour. Cover; let rise in a warm place. Work down and make out into rolls or loaves. Let rise. Bake rolls at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Bake loaves at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all wet ingredients together.
Pour over Stove Top.
Bake at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Combine mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, Ranch Style beans and milk.
Brown ground meat and add taco seasoning. Grate Cheddar cheese and quarter flour tortillas.
Layer tortillas, meat, 1/2 sauce and top with cheese.
Repeat.

title: pork and bean bake
directions: Mix all together and place in greased casserole dish.
Put in oven and bake at 400°.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add in eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Mix in flour and nuts.
Spread mixture into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, then cut into bars.
Sift top with confectioners sugar.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Crisco until smooth.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well, add flour and milk, beat about 5 minutes.
Add baking powder.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 loaf
or 1 tube pan that has been greased and lined with wax paper.
Cook at 350° one hour or until tester comes out clean when stuck in cake.
Cool in pans about 10 minutes.
Take out of pans.
Put in a tight container until cold.

title: austin spanish rice
directions: Saute rice in oleo until light brown. Saute meat, onion and pepper until meat is done. Add salt, pepper, cumin, tomatoes and chili powder.
Mix together and add water.
Cook for 5 minutes and then mix in rice mixture.
Place in a covered casserole dish. Bake, covered, 1 to 1 1/4 hours in a 350° oven.
Serve with a green salad and hot garlic French bread.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cut lettuce in 1-inch pieces and put on bottom of dish, then layer celery, green pepper and onion, all chopped or diced.
Layer thawed peas.
Mix mayonnaise with sugar and layer.
Top with grated cheese.
Put bacon, fried and crumbled, on the top; refrigerate.
Make the night before needed or at least 8 hours in advance.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and celery together until tender.
Melt cheese in microwave dish.
Mix into melted cheese, soup, rice, cooked broccoli and celery.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Heat in microwave and serve.

title: dex cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: great grandmother costa's applesauce cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Add raisins, nuts, applesauce and oil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: quick dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
3/4 cup warm water; set aside.
In large mixing
bowl
combine
warm
milk and water.
Add salt, sugar
and oil; mix well.
Add flour, yeast and water mixture; mix
well. Knead
it
with
your hands.
Coat your hands with shortening
to knead
the
dough.
Wet a towel in cold water; wring it
out good. Cover dough.
Set in a warm place and let stand for
hour. Push it down; let it stand for 10 minutes more.
Make your rolls or loaves.
Cover and let stand in warm place
until
double
in size.
Bake in prewarmed oven at 240° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: eggs newport
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix mayonnaise and soup in saucepan over low heat, slowly adding milk until mixed and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Put small amount of sauce in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Slice eggs in circles and layer on top of sauce.
Sprinkle with some green onions and bacon.
Repeat layer with sauce, eggs, onions and bacon.
You should have at least 3 layers with top layer sprinkled with bacon.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (30 to 40 minutes).
Serve over biscuits.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Melt margarine and add onion, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Slice rolls in half.
Spread mixture on bottom half of rolls.
Put ham and cheese on top of mixture. Spread remaining mixture on top half of rolls.
Place top on cheese.
Place back in roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.
Brown in oil.
Add garlic, salt and bouillon.
Simmer 1 hour.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into pan.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Stir lemon juice with milk.
Add crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cut up margarine over sweet potatoes; sprinkle sugar, salt and cinnamon over potatoes.
Pour orange juice or apricot nectar over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.

title: go to bed meringues
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, but not until stiff.
Add sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold in Rice Krispies and chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoon, about 40, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 1 minute.
Turn oven off.
Do not open the door.
Leave in the oven overnight.

title: taco burgers
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, sugar and dry mustard.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, until thickened, 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture onto toasted buns.
Sprinkle each of the burgers with lettuce and cheese.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: liz's shrimp creole
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp and cook slowly.
Stir occasionally.
The last thirty minutes, add shrimp.

title: apple betty pie
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with orange juice.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all together in order in large bowl.
Stir once every 1/2 hour for 5 1/2 hours to coat crackers.
Then eat and enjoy!

title: beans and wiener basket
directions: Put beans in a casserole dish.
Add onion soup mix, brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Mix well.
Cut hot dogs in half crosswise.
Stand them up around edge of casserole.
Place bacon across beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seafood fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Beat eggs and yogurt together.
Melt butter and toss with hot fettuccine over low heat.
Add a little of the cheese at a time while continuing to stir.
Add egg and yogurt mixture and toss over low heat until cheeses are blended together.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts; split in half.
Put each piece between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Pound to twice the original size using a wooden mallet or bottom of bottle.
Cut ham and cheese slices in half.
Fold chicken piece in half with ham and cheese sandwiched between halves.
Seal edges of chicken by pounding together.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix together and put cheese on top. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 12 pan. Mix buttermilk, self-rising flour and sugar. Pour over melted butter. Take water and mix jello. Add to cherry pie filling and pour over batter. Swirl through the batter and bake at 350° until done.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, sugar and onion.
Add milk and egg and mix well. Drop rounded teaspoonful in hot fat (375°); fry only a few at a time until golden brown.

title: english trifle
directions: Arrange sponge cake in bottom of dish.
Spread jam on top. Pour strained fruit on top.
Mix jello; cool and pour over cake and fruit.
Let stand several hours.
Cook vanilla pudding; cool and pour on top of hardened jello. Cover with whipping cream and grated chocolate bar.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Simmer thinly
sliced carrots until tender; drain.
Melt butter; stir in flour, then add milk, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat and add grated cheese and parsley.
Add carrots.
Place in a quart casserole or baking dish, greased.
Mix melted butter and corn flakes and sprinkle over the top.
If you are using glass, bake at 350°
for 50 minutes. Otherwise, bake at 375°.

title: applesauce raisin cake
directions: Mix all.
Bake in sprayed 9-inch square pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth in a large mixing bowl.
Sift in Bisquick and mix well.
Chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
Heat oven to 350°.
After chilling is done, shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet.
Dip fork in sugar and crisscross to flatten balls.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.

title: our favorite chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in greased casserole dish.
Pour in the broth and the soup over the chicken.
Add the mixed vegetables and peas.

title: boss hog burger
directions: Cook patties as desired.
Top with remaining ingredients. Serve on 5-inch bun.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together thoroughly and store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup (4 heaping teaspoonfuls) to 1 cup hot water.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and curry in oil until tender. Add apple, carrots, celery and green pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add flour and coat vegetables.
Add broth, undrained tomatoes, parsley, lemon, sugar, cloves, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil.
Add chicken and simmer 30 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: easy stew
directions: Layer ingredients in Dutch oven or heavy pot with a lid.
Cook in oven 6 to 8 hours.
Do not stir and keep covered on 275°.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion; cook 1 minute. Add the garlic and ham; cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Reduce the heat. Add the celery, thyme and bay leaf; cook, covered, over medium-low heat for 5 minutes. Remove the cover and add the potatoes; toss well. Add the chicken broth. Heat to boiling; reduce the heat. Simmer, uncovered, until the potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Remove the soup from the heat; stir in the parsley. Combine the sour cream with 1/2 cup of the soup in a small bowl. Whisk this mixture back into the soup. Serve immediately. Serves 2 as a main course, 4 as a first course.

title: josephinas
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Grate cheese coarsely and beat with butter.
Put garlic through garlic press (or mash or mince finely).
Add chilies and garlic to cheese mixture.
Add mayonnaise.
Beat well to blend.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator.

title: payday cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl and mix on low speed until crumbly.

Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased glass pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until brown. Remove and immediately sprinkle with the marshmallows. Return to the oven for 1 to 2 minutes (until marshmallows "puff"). Cool and prepare topping.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add beef and onion and cook, stirring with fork to break up meat, until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add macaroni and spaghetti sauce; stir to blend.
In 2-quart casserole, layer macaroni mixture alternately with cheese and pepperoni, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.

title: fabulous punch
directions: Boil sugar with water for 3 minutes; let cool.
Combine all ingredients, except sherbet and ginger ale; stir into syrup.
Put in punch bowl over crushed ice.
Add sherbet and ginger ale just prior to serving.
Serves 30.

title: rollups
directions: Layer flour tortillas on a baking sheet. Layer turkey, zucchini, onion, and cheese. Roll up and bake at 350 for 10 minutes. Slice into wedges and serve.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs until fluffy.
Sift all dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add mashed potatoes to sugar mixture, then dry ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: kathy's veggie dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with fresh, raw vegetables.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In small bowl, mix mayonnaise and sugar until sugar melts. Cover and seal salad with mixture.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Best if served next day.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Stir
together	flour,	sugar,	baking powder and salt. Make a hole in center and add oil, egg yolks and orange juice. Mix in bowl
until
smooth.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and	salt until
stiff
with mixer.
Blend top ingredients in with egg whites lightly, using a spatula. I use an angel food cake pan to bake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Top with
butter frosting
with 1 tablespoon orange juice.
Delicious.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and pour off fat.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Garnish with bacon slices.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: poor man's pasta
directions: Boil cabbage until almost tender.
Coat pan with olive oil. Brown onion and garlic.
Drain cabbage thoroughly and add to onion and garlic.
Fry cabbage until light brown, breaking up the flowerets.
Add about a tablespoon of water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and let simmer.
Cook your spaghetti to taste. Drain spaghetti.
Top with the cabbage.
Serves 4. Cooking time is 1 hour.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Lightly grease a large Bundt pan.
Layer frozen rolls in pan. Mix cinnamon and sugar and pour over rolls.
Layer one at a time, chopped nuts, brown sugar and dry pudding mix.
Slice margarine and place around rolls.
Cover pan with cloth and set in warm place overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert pan, let sit a few minutes, then remove.
Pour remaining syrup over cake. Serves 10 to 14.

title: orange mold(no water jell-o type)
directions: Mix orange Jell-O with cottage cheese.
(Do not use according to directions on Jell-O box.)
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add drained pineapple and orange sections; fold in until well mixed. Mold and refrigerate until firmly set.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and cut into strips. Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients.
Gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine 3 tablespoons of butter and stuffing mix. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Reserve 2 3/4 cups of broth.

Combine chicken soup with broth; mix well and set aside. Combine stuffing mix and butter; reserve 1/4 cup for garnish. Spoon half of remaining stuffing mixture in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of chicken.
Cover with chicken soup mixture; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white until very stiff.
Add soda and sugar; mix well.
Add pecans and stir until coated.
Spoon 1 puff at a time on a slightly greased cookie sheet and bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown.
Let stand and cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: raisin-nut cake mix cookies
directions: Just mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Drop them on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Strain shrimp in cold water and drain. Thaw. Mix all ingredients, then add shrimp.
Make several days in advance to enhance flavor. Serve with crackers.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add soups, tomato sauce, green chiles and 2 teaspoons chili powder; mix together.
Cut tortillas in fourths.
Place 1 layer tortillas in bottom of 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon a layer of beef mixture over tortillas. Continue layering tortillas and beef ending with beef on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: nutty chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Chill. Serve on lettuce cups.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peg's stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes. While hot, scoop out into bowl. Add all ingredients to potato. Beat with electric mixer until almost smooth.
Put back into shells (potato skins).
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°. Sprinkle with paprika before heating.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Serve on salad greens. Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and fold in potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: duff's fruit bread
directions: Mix all together and beat with electric mixer for 4 minutes. Bake in 9 x 14-inch pan or two (5 x 9-inch) pans at 425° until lightly brown and coming away from edge of pan.
Two cups of broken walnuts, pecans or almonds may be added, if desired.

title: cherry oatmeal bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar for 10 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Spread 2/3 of dough in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling mixed with coconut evenly over entire surface.
Cover with remaining dough and pat down.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Makes 24 (2-inch) bars.

title: pecan chess pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, granulated sugar and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake just until set at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve slightly warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, pineapple, nuts, oil and bananas.
Stir. Do not beat.
Bake at 350° until done in center.

title: corn cakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add
meal,	flour,	salt, baking powder and butter.
Add enough milk to make a thin batter.
Pour onto hot griddle and
flip
to other side when brown.
Good with honey, syrup or molasses.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Place each piece of fish on piece of foil.
Top with mushrooms.
Add salt, pepper, paprika and lemon juice.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Top each fish piece with about 1/4 cup of sauce. Sprinkle with parsley.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: For crust, put graham cracker crumbs in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt butter and sugar together and pour over crumbs. Press crumb mixture with a fork into pan.

For cake, soften cream cheese and second stick of butter to room temperature and combine them with vanilla and powered sugar. Spread carefully over crumbs. Top by arranging the bananas on cream cheese and sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration. Spread pineapple over bananas. Spread Cool Whip, sprinkle nuts and arrange cherries on top. Chill until set.

title: raspberry upside cake
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup sugar; add egg and beat well.
Stir in the flavoring.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Spoon in cherries.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl, stirring until smooth.
Pour over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 1 hour.

title: d.o. stroganoff
directions: Brown meat
in oil in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add everything else,
except
rice and mushrooms.	Mix well, cover and cook for 2 1/2
hours
or until meat is tender.
Add rice and mushrooms and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough and place on round pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden. Cool completely. Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over crust. Drain the orange and pineapple juices into small saucepan. Add tapioca and cook until thick. Arrange fruit over spread, then pour the juice glaze. Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak together the first 2 ingredients for 1 hour.
Mix thoroughly the next 3 ingredients.
Sift together the next 4 ingredients, then combine all and put into 12-cup muffin pan.
May use paper muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place bacon, cheese and onion in a lightly greased 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Blend remaining ingredients in a blender at high speed for 10 seconds.
Pour over bacon, cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes and serve.

title: green chili stew
directions: Chop
meat in small cubes and fry with bacon drippings. When meat
is
pretty
well
done,
add flour and brown.
Add chopped tomato
and let fry for a few minutes.
Add chili and enough
warm water
to make soft gravy.
Add garlic and salt; let simmer for a few minutes.

title: chocolate and fruit trifle
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions; pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Crumble enough cake to measure 8 cups; set aside.
Save remaining cake for another use. In a mixing bowl, combine milk and water until smooth.
Add pudding mix; beat on low speed for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fold in the whipped cream.
To assemble, spread 2 1/2 cups pudding mixture in a 4 quart glass bowl.
Top with half of the crumbled cake; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon orange juice. Arrange half of the berries and kiwi over cake.
Repeat pudding and cake layers; sprinkle with remaining orange juice.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Spoon remaining fruit around edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yield: 12-16 servings.

title: walnut clusters
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until very light and fluffy.
With mixer at low speed, mix in chocolate, then flour mixture.
Fold in walnuts. Drop by teaspoon 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes-no longer.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cheesy pineapple casserole
directions: Save 12 tablespoons juice from pineapple. Mix the sugar, flour and pineapple juice. Fold in the pineapple chunks and grated cheese. Pour into melted margarine. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix well and put in 2-quart casserole.

title: cindy's chicken
directions: Mix flour, seasoned salt, pepper and basil together.
Roll and coat chicken breast thoroughly.
Save remaining flour mixture. Lightly brown chicken in olive oil and remove chicken from pan. Take chicken bouillon cube and place in 1 cup very hot water until it dissolves.
Stir wine and cup of bouillon into the drippings in the pan, stirring until it is fairly smooth, and bring to a boil (might have to add a little water).
Place chicken in a deep, flat dish.
Place mushrooms and onions over chicken.
Pour mixture from pan over chicken and bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Very tender!!!!

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a pan.

title: deviled chicken spread
directions: Combine all the ingredients until well blended.
Chill, if desired, before serving.
Use as sandwich spread.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Combine fruit and sugar.
Let stand for 20 minutes stirring occasionally.
Boil pectin and water rapidly for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add berries and stir 2 minutes.
Pour into containers and cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Refrigerate until set.
Store in freezer. Makes 5 to 6 half pints.

title: fat-free milk shake
directions: Mix well in blender.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, milk and flour and mix well.
Cook in a heavy boiler until slightly thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine and let cool.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Crumble sausage in oil and fry until done.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir with a fork.
Pour milk and water into mixture. Keep stirring until gravy thickens.
Spoon over hot biscuits or toast.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook until small ball will form when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Before taking from heat, add marshmallows.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix ingredients and place in casserole dish. Bake at 375° about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Cook beef and onions until beef is lightly browned.
Core and cut cabbage into 1-inch strips.
Stir in cabbage.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until cabbage wilts.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes until cabbage is tender. Serve with rice.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti with asparagus
directions: Heat butter and oil in 1 quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion and saute until golden (do not brown).
Add ham and saute briefly.
Add asparagus, water, and bouillon cube.
Reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti to large pot of rapidly boiling salted water and cook until al dente, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain well.
Return spaghetti to pot.
Add asparagus mixture and half and half; cook over medium-low heat until warmed through.
Top with Parmesan and pepper before serving.

title: fried rice
directions: Sautee the green onions and green pepper in the bacon fat until transparent.
Add the rice, bacon, 2 tablespoons of Soy Sauce, eggs and clams or seafood.
Heat just enough for the flavors to combine.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce in small pieces.
Place in glass 9 x 12-inch dish, then put in layers celery, peas, pepper, eggs, onion and bacon.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over like icing.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Top with canned biscuits or homemade dough for crust.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: cheese stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, milk, garlic salt, salt, pepper, grated onion, cooked rice and ground beef.
Press half of mixture into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Place cheese on top.
Spread rest of meat mixture over the top, pressing to seal cheese in.
Pour barbecue sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: pear-cream cheese spread
directions: Combine pear preserves and horseradish; spoon over cream cheese.
Serve with gingersnaps, crackers or date-nut bread.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Place vegetables in slow cooker.
In small bowl, combine soup, water, poultry seasoning, onion powder and bouillon.
Blend well; pour over half of mixture over vegetables.
Top with chicken breasts; pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.

title: christmas chili
directions: Combine the hamburger, corn, diced tomatoes, salsa and kidney beans in frying pan. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or warm French bread.

title: broccoli chicken rice
directions: Cook the rice by directions on box.
Steam broccoli by directions.
Drain rice.
Put in medium mixing bowl.
Combine rice, broccoli and soup.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut cheese into thin slices.
Place all over top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Drop mixture by tablespoonful into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.

title: onion pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine until translucent.
Crush enough crackers in a pie plate to cover bottom and sides.
Pour onions and butter over crackers.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gingered orange and kiwi fruit fluff
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat heavy or whipping cream and sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in ginger, peel and slice kiwi fruit.
Arrange kiwi fruit and orange in 6 dessert dishes.
Top with cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together; form into balls and dip in chocolate. Use toothpick to hold balls while dipping. Use chocolate syrup as dip.

title: chocolate gooey bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and combine with cake mix. Pat in jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch).
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and cereal.
Drizzle condensed milk evenly over top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cereal is golden brown.
While bars are warm, run knife around sides of pan to loosen edges.
Cool 2 hours.
Cut into about 2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yields 48 bars.

title: cottage pie
directions: In a casserole dish or pie plate, put the ground beef, then put in creamed corn.
Mix mashed potatoes according to package. Place mashed potatoes on top (should look like whipped cream). Sprinkle with salt and pepper on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until creamed corn comes through top.

title: punch bowl trifle
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set the pineapple aside. Prepare cake batter according to package directions, substituting pineapple juice for the water.
(Add water if necessary for the required measurement.)
Bake as directed in a greased 13x9x2 inch pan.
Cool.
Meanwhile, prepare pudding according to package directions.
Cut the cake into 1 inch cubes; place half in a 6 qt. punch bowl.
Top with half of the pudding, pie filling, pineapple, bananas, fruit cocktail, oranges, whipped topping and coconut. Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar, peanut butter and melted butter.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Using hands, form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a baking dish.
Heat at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with Waverly crackers for spreading or Doritos to dip.

title: six weeks slaw
directions: Bring the last 3 ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: Add all ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken ole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Drain if necessary.
Spoon salsa over chicken; top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Saute green pepper in the oil over medium heat until softened. Add scallions and chicken and continue cooking until meat is done.
Stir in chili powder.
Remove from heat.
Grease a 9-inch glass pie pan.
Place 1 tortilla on bottom of pan; spoon on 1/3 of the salsa, 1/3 of chicken mixture, 1/3 of olives and 1/4 of shredded cheese.

Repeat this sequence for 2 more layers. Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top of the fourth tortilla and arrange cherry tomatoes, cut side down, around the edge of dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: orange delight
directions: Fold all ingredients together, chill before serving.
For fewer calories, use low-fat cottage cheese, unsweetened pineapple and sugar-free gelatin.

title: famous peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to 250° on candy thermometer.
Add butter and peanuts.
Stir constantly and cook to 310°.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda.
Pour onto buttered aluminum tray or pans (must use aluminum).
Stretch and break into pieces.
(I always have the peanuts and butter ready to add; I have the pans ready; start pouring onto pans as soon as soda is mixed; and take phone off the hook!
Must work fast!)

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute chopped sausage in olive oil; add strained olives, sofrito (Spanish seasonings), pigeon peas, oregano, bay leaves, tomato sauce and con azafran.
Mix well, then add rice and stir. Add 1 cup of hot water and bring to boil; keep adding water this way until rice is covered in water.
Bring to boil; cover, then turn burner to lowest setting and let simmer 30 minutes.
Do not take cover off!
Rice will stick to bottom of pan, that's okay. Spanish seasonings can be found in the international section of your store.
The sofrito should be fresh or frozen for best results.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix meat, soup, sour cream and chiles together.
Spread a thin layer of chicken mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Fill flour tortillas with the mixture. Roll each tortilla up and place in pan, seam side down.
