Make sure to leave some mixture to spread over top of filled tortillas.
Cover with mixture, then cheese and olives.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken up as if to fry.
Mix all other ingredients over low heat until well mixed.
Coat each piece of chicken by dipping into sauce and place in baking dish.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and put in large pot.
Add vinegar and salt; boil 10 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Put remaining ingredients into a large jar; add mushrooms and shake to coat well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef or turkey; drain fat.
Stir in chili seasoning, tomato sauce and kidney beans.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: mock liver pate
directions: Mash liverwurst with a fork.
Mix in garlic salt, basil and onion.
Flatten bottom after shaping into a ball. Frost ball with cream cheese and sprinkle with parsley or nuts.
It is best to make this the night before so seasonings can blend.
Very good.

title: beef ball casserole supreme
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and roll into balls; brown and place in casserole.
Combine water and tomato puree.
Thicken with flour and water.
Add sour cream and pour over balls.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: uncooked peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until dissolved.
Stir constantly.
Don't boil.
Take off heat immediately and stir in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Spoon out on waxed paper.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: zucchini medley
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Saute in pan with butter, sprinkle with seasonings.
Sprinkle with garlic and cook until soft.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size pieces.
Place all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Toss in half of the dressing and mix thoroughly.
Before ready to serve, add the rest of the dressing according to taste.
Warning: Makes a lot of pasta salad once all thrown together.
Serves a crowd.
Can be prepared a day ahead.

title: wooey gooey cake
directions: Mix together and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: braided bread
directions: Combine water, yeast and 1 cup flour.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, oil and 2 cups flour along with salt.
Now add to original mixture.
Add remaining flour, 2 to 3 cups, enough to make dough elastic.
Knead.
Place in a greased bowl and turn so all sides are coated with oil.
Cover.
Let rise until double in size. Punch down.
Divide dough in thirds.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cook in large saucepan until it forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Then add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour nuts in as it thickens.
Pour onto a greased platter.
Put in refrigerator until cold, then cut into squares.

title: taco dip
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and taco sauce to your taste. Spread on a large platter.
Top with layer of taco sauce and refrigerate.
Add lettuce, tomato, onion, Cheddar cheese and black olives over the top. Serve with taco chips.

title: hot crab meat dip
directions: Mix well and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix ham, potatoes, carrots, onions, parsley and flour in a large greasy oven-proof dish.
Top with bacon.
Cover and cook 45 minutes at 400°.
Uncover the last 5 minutes so bacon will crisp.

title: praline pecan pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add pecans and coconut; brown lightly.
Mix cream cheese, milk and Cool Whip together.
Pour 1/4 of cream mixture into each crust, followed by 1/4 coconut/pecan mixture and 1/4 caramel topping.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil and place in freezer.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cheese and sugar; add berries, pineapple, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Serve frozen.

title: bacon-wieners
directions: Cut each wiener into thirds and each piece bacon in half. Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around 1/3 of wiener and secure with toothpick.
Put in the bottom of crock-pot and add dry brown sugar on top of all this.
Cook on low heat 3 to 4 hours or until bacon is done.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 dish.
In microwave on low power, cook chocolate chips and butter for 5 minutes.
With an electric mixer, mix the powdered sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add microwaved ingredients. Pour into dish.
Let set.
Cut into squares.
May refrigerate to harden.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: orange slush
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Fill up with ice cubes. Put on speed to chop ice cubes.
Serve.
Delicious!

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, Twin brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples. Chop oleo and add to mixture.
Add apple juice.
Top with thawed pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian stroganoff
directions: Mix flour and salt; coat beef stew meat with flour mixture; cook and stir onion and garlic in shortening in 10-inch skillet until onion is tender.
Remove from skillet.
Cook and stir beef in same skillet until brown.
Stir in onion, garlic, water, tomato sauce, mushrooms, instant bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 1 hour.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingerbread people
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix dark brown sugar and butter. Beat in egg and molasses.
Stir in flour, ginger, baking soda and remaining spices.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in boiler.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes about 5 dozen depending on cookie size.

title: raisin cake
directions: Place butter in mixing bowl in oven and warm to soften.
Blend in sugar.
Add eggs one at a time while mixing slowly.
Add salt, flavoring and flour, blending well.
Stir in raisins with mixing spoon.
Batter will be stiff.
This prevents raisins from settling to bottom.
Makes a large tube cake.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: easy party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars. Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well. Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's; reserve remaining candy for decorating.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops with remaining candy.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Fry up sausage and set aside.
Blend all other ingredients except sausage and dripping.
Blend ingredients in blender on high speed for 1 minute.
Transfer into saucepan and cook on medium heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add sausage and 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Pour over hot biscuits.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: To make 10 quarts of pickles:
Make a solution of 2 quarts of vinegar, 6 quarts water, 2 cups pickling salt.
Bring mixture to boiling point.
Pack pickles in quart jars.
Pour mixture over pickles very slowly.
Allow jars to stand until pickles turn color, 5 to 10 minutes.
Then pour off the solution from jars back into your kettle so you can use again for rest of pickles.
Always reheat to boiling point.
Have another kettle ready of the same solution.
Allow to boil, pour over pickles in jar, covering them well.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with nuts and coconut, that have been mixed together.
Mix German chocolate cake according to box directions and pour on top of nuts and coconut.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into rectangular glass dish.
Cover and freeze.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: best ever cake
directions: Stir well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost cake as soon as it comes from the oven.
Let cool and refrigerate at least two days.
Can be frozen after being refrigerated.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars. Add extracts. Stir in eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients. Chill; roll into balls smaller than walnuts; flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add water.
Cook until mixture is clear red.
Stir in 1/2 tablespoon red food coloring.
When mixture is lukewarm, add 2 boxes of strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.

title: mrs. popik's baked in cake filling
directions: Mix all together, excluding nuts and powdered sugar, until smooth.
Pour 1/2 to 2/3 of batter on greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with filling.
Spoon rest of batter over the filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with nuts and powdered sugar, when cool.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Topping) and mix by hand.
Do not use an electric mixer.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Spread topping over cake while warm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: camp-out fruit cobbler
directions: Butter inside of a 10-inch cast-iron skillet or Dutch oven. Pour in pie filling. Pour cake mix on top. Evenly dot top of cake mix with thin slices of butter.
Scoop out a hole in fire and place pan with liquid in coals.
Push coals around pan and place some on top. Leave in fire 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from fire. Serve warm.
In oven, bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta shells florentine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix spinach, cheeses, egg white, Parmesan and nutmeg until blended.
Fill cooked shells with heaping tablespoonful of spinach mixture.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: jalapeno cheese bake
directions: Cook rice; chop peppers and mix with sour cream in top of food processor, then stir in rice, sour cream and pepper mixture with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in 1/2 stick margarine.
Let cool.
Add cooked onions to grated Swiss cheese.
Butter pan and spread crushed saltine crackers on bottom.
Add onion-cheese mixture and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Bake at 325° until set.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Mix together with fork.
For a smoother dip, mix in blender. Serve with raw vegetable sticks (celery, cucumber, green pepper, zucchini, etc).
Yields 4 servings.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers in half and place in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Mix rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over crackers. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix well and make into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Chill and serve.

title: jello pie
directions: Boil pineapple juice, Jell-O and sugar.
Beat milk until like whipped cream; pour in mixture.
Put in pie shells and chill.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown sausage; add onion and peppers and saute.
Add broth, garlic, parsley, oregano, basil and tomatoes.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cooked pasta and serve with grated cheese.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower for about 20 minutes or until it is tender but crisp.
Blend mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, lemon juice, salt, mustard and parsley.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mayonnaise mixture.
Cover cauliflower with sauce and bake about 15 minutes in 350° oven or until frosting begins to brown.
Can be prepared early in the day except for final baking.
Serves six.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in vanilla.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add mincemeat, apple butter and nuts, mix thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold flour mixture into batter. Line bottom of a greased tube pan with waxed paper; grease paper.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: zesty baked chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and sprinkle over both sides of chicken; place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/4 cup yogurt and soy sauce; brush half over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken over; brush with remaining yogurt mixture and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup yogurt and flour; stir well and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lola's vegetable soup
directions: Rinse frozen vegetables.
Combine all ingredients in a large cooking pot on medium
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Then simmer another 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve with cornbread.
Makes about 16 to 20 servings.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: In largest bowl of electric mixer, cream 1 cup of butter with shortening and sugar until mixture is fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir flour with baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Add vanilla and stir in pineapple and juice; blend well. Spoon batter into well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Do not use smaller pan. Place in cold oven, then set temperature at 325°. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake springs back when lightly touched. Remove from oven and let stand about 5 minutes in pan. Loosen cake around edges with knife and invert carefully onto cake rack. In blender or food processor, combine remaining 1/4 cup butter, confectioners sugar and drained pineapple. Process until smooth and pour over cake while it's still warm. Let cool before slicing. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cornmeal mix in medium bowl. In small bowl, stir together milk, oil and eggs.
Pour liquid into dry mixture.
Stir just enough to mix everything together good.
I like to heat an iron skillet on top of the stove with 1 tablespoon oil while I mix batter.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned on top, about 20 to 30 minutes depending on the size of the skillet.

title: double-crust pizza casserole
directions: For crust, combine flour, potatoes, milk and margarine.
Set aside.

title: lite and tasty dilly chicken sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread and sprouts.
Cut pita bread in half.
Spoon mixture into pocket.
Top with sprouts. Serves 4.

title: dried beef gravy dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into a loaf of bread (with inside pulled out).
Use inside pieces of bread for dipping into the dip.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Stir gently to mix.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, dressing and mayo.
Top cooled crescent rolls.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Garnish with green stuffed olives. Spread on crackers or party bread slices.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Cut raw asparagus in bite size pieces.
Pour Italian dressing over asparagus; marinate overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs well in bowl.
Stir in sugars, oats, coconut, milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
This pie is easy to make.
It's flavor resembles a pecan pie.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak in small strips.
Brown in drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Mushrooms may be added, if desired.

title: corn oysters
directions: Stir flour into beaten egg; add to corn with butter and seasoning.
Drop by spoonful onto hot, greased griddle and cook to delicate brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Let set.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mixture with banana slices and wafers.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in a double boiler and beat with eggbeater for 7 minutes.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread on cake.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Press two-thirds of dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread preserves; crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, cut into squares and serve.
Yields 36 bars.

title: southern chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat chocolate, butter and coffee in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Combine sugar and syrup in another saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Reduce heat and boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate mixture.
Pour slowly over eggs, stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is completely puffed across top. Cool.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat oil; gradually add sugar and eggs (one at a time). Add spices
and
salt.	Add
flour
and milk alternately.
Add jam, jelly and
pecans.	Bake
in tube pan at 325° until firm. Pour glaze on while cake is hot.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, heat first 4 ingredients until carrots are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, corn and cauliflower.
Heat through. Just before serving, stir in the cheese and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour pan.
Cream butter with sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg. Add sour cream.
Add sifted flour and soda in small amounts, beating constantly.
Stir in vanilla and almond.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes to 1 1/2 hours.

title: 2 peanut butter pies
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add Cool Whip, one bowl at a time, mixing well.
Add sugar, mix well.
Last, add peanut butter and mix.
Place filling in crust.
Sprinkle with coconut or slices of banana.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook until dry the water and rice.
Use a double boiler. After rice is cooked dry, add milk, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and cook.
Stir and watch.
If you like raisins, add 1/2 cup.

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat from broth, reserving broth; cool meat completely.
Skin, bone and chop chicken.
Coarsely chop meat; set aside.
Skim off and discard fat from surface of broth.
Measure broth and return 3 quarts to Dutch oven.
Add chopped meats and remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 4 hours, stirring often.
Add additional reserved broth and water if necessary.
Discard red pepper pod. Yields 5 quarts.

title: crisp little lemon cookies
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Add Rice Krispies cereal, margarine and egg.
Shape into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet; press flat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 9 to 12 minutes, or until light brown around edges.
Cool and remove.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: beef and rice-a-roni
directions: Brown onions and hamburger meat.
Cook Rice-A-Roni per directions on box.
Mix hamburger and Rice-A-Roni.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop mushroom stems.
In a skillet, heat 1 tablespoon butter and add onion and chopped stems.
Cook 2 minutes. Add crumbs, bacon, seasonings and enough cream or sherry to moisten.
Place mushroom caps on baking sheet, cap side up, and brush with some of the melted remaining butter.
Broil about 2 minutes.
Turn over; stuff with filling and brush with butter again and broil about 3 or 4 minutes.

title: honey mustard potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss in potatoes.
Chill at least 15 minutes. Toss again before serving.
Serves 6.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in jar; cover tightly.
Place 2 teaspoons in a cup of boiling water to serve.
Great warm-up on cold days.

title: strawberry milk shake
directions: Crush strawberries and press through a coarse sieve; there should be at least 1 2/3 cups puree.
Combine with milk and cream; add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill well before serving.
Top each glass with a spoonful of whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix butter, flour, egg and sugar.
Add milk to make batter. Mix together good.
Dip onion rings into the batter.
Fry in deep fryer with hot grease.
Cook until desired browness.

title: spinach bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix together eggs, flour, milk and baking powder until smooth. Stir in spinach, onion, finely chopped crumbled bacon, cheese and mushrooms.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with crushed onion rings.	Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes until golden brown.
Cool slightly. Cut in small squares or large squares for dinner vegetables.
This reheats well.

title: cheese-pimiento rolls
directions: Scald milk and cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixer bowl, pour milk and water mixture.
Add 1 1/4 cups flour, shortening, sugar, salt and egg.
Beat one minute.
Add cheese, pepper, pimiento and 1 cup flour; mix.
Beat one minute, spoon in prepared muffin tins and let rise until double in bulk or about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes.
Rolls may be frozen.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured cake pans; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine and beat until smooth.
Use a large deep skillet and fill about 2/3 full of oil.
Heat oil.
When the oil is hot, take a funnel that has a spout 1/2-inch in diameter.
Be sure to put your finger over the funnel hole as you pour the batter into the funnel.
Hold funnel over hot oil.
Starting in the middle of the skillet let the batter come out of the funnel hole, making a circular motion, making circles with the batter.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Then bake for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie (custard)
directions: Mix all ingredients adding eggs last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, sugar, egg, and raisins and put in greased casserole dish.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add grits, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add margarine, cheese, egg and milk mixture to grits.
Mix well.

title: carrot wheat bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and margarine with the scalded milk.
Cool to lukewarm. In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk to yeast mixture, egg, whole-wheat flour and 1 cup white flour.
Mix until smooth.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar with cornstarch and salt in large saucepan. Gradually whisk in milk until smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring gently, over medium-high heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a long pan.
Pour peaches on top, saving 1 cup of juice.
Cook at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes. When done, pour remaining juice on top and serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease sheet cake pan.
Pour chopped pecans in and spread, then spread coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix 1 stick of melted margarine, softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed franks
directions: Combine cheese, pickle, mustard and onion to make a paste. Make a slit lengthwise in each hot dog.
Fill each slit with paste mixture.
Wrap hot dogs with bacon slices and secure with toothpicks.
Broil, cheese side down, 3 minutes and turn. Continue to broil until bacon is crisp.
Serve on buns.

title: pande elate
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except chilies and cheese.
Mix well. Turn half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Cover with chilies, then cheese slices. Spread remaining batter over cheese.
May be mixed early in the day and refrigerated at this point. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: brown rice pudding
directions: In saucepan heat brown rice, milk and sugar until sugar is dissolved and mixture is hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat. In bowl combine 1/2 cup hot milk mixture and eggs.
Slowly stir egg mixture back into milk mixture.
Cook over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes until custard is just thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and orange peel.
Cover and chill 1 hour until thickened.
Serve in 6 parfait or tall glasses, alternate layers of raspberries and pudding.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: thick and saucy chili
directions: In large soup pot, brown the ground beef in the oil.
Drain excess grease. Add the remaining ingredients except the cornstarch.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Add enough water to the cornstarch to make a paste that will pour. Add to chili and cook until thickened.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in a saucepan coated with vegetable cooking spray over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes until tender.
Stir in chicken broth, chopped potato, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Combine cornstarch and milk, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to potato mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir in corn and chopped pimento.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly, 1 minute or until thickened.
Serve immediately.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar and flour; blend until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until brown in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Shape ground round with onion into small meatballs; brown slowly.
Drain on paper towel; arrange in large freezing dish. Place jelly and catsup in saucepan; heat until melted.
Add garlic powder and parsley.
Mix well; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over meatballs; cover with foil and freeze.
Place in 350° oven 30 minutes before use.
Keep foil cover on until heated.
Place in chafing dish to serve.
Yields 35 to 40 meatballs.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown chicken in margarine; remove from pan.
Brown onion and green pepper.
Add chicken bouillon, salt and paprika.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and cook until tender.
Combine tomato soup and flour.
When chicken is tender, add tomato soup mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add sour cream; blend well.
Cover and cook a few more minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Debone salmon; reserve liquid.
Mix salmon, liquid and other ingredients.
Add enough flour and cornmeal to make mixture dough-like.
Fry in hot oil.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Whip up at each serving.

title: italian pasta salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix lime juice, mustard, mayonnaise, seasoning, cheese and ham. Mix well.
Add pasta.
(I use ham labeled 95% fat-free.)
Like garlic?
Add to taste!

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter with hands, then form into balls.
Chill in refrigerator for 45 minutes.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Insert toothpicks in balls and dip in chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: divine raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in the boiling pineapple juice and water (1 cup).
Pour over marshmallows and cream cheese.
Beat with mixer.
In another bowl, whip cream.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add to jello mixture.

title: waldorf salad(serves 4)
directions: Core and dice apples. Sprinkle lemon juice. Add celery and walnuts. Toss to mix.

title: bow ties with sausage and sweet peppers
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Return to saucepan.
Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and cook sausage with peppers in skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Stir broth and black pepper into skillet.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Pour over pasta; add parsley.
Toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
In large container for freezing, combine pineapple juice, lemon juice, frozen lemonade and frozen orange juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let boiled mixture cool somewhat; pour into container and mix all well.
Freeze.
Put frozen mixture in punch bowl and pour in about 1/2 to 1 can Sprite and rum.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, toss chocolate wafer crumbs with water, a teaspoon at a time, until crumbs are moistened. Press onto bottom of 8-inch springform pan; set aside.

title: heaven's delight cake
directions: Mix together and bake in layer pans at 350° until done.
Cool completely.

title: lattice topped blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and orange peel.
Lightly toss with blueberries.
Place in pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Dot top with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry. Cut into 1/2 inch strips.
Arrange in lattice pattern on top of pie.
Moisten edge of lower crust; fold over lattice ends.
Seal and flute.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling begins to bubble.

title: marbled cheesecake
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add first 6 ingredients.
Process until smooth; set aside.
Combine hot water and espresso granules in small bowl.
Split ladyfingers in half lengthwise.
Quickly dip 20 ladyfinger halves, cut side down, in espresso; place dipped side down, in the bottom of a 9-inch square baking dish.
Dip 20 more ladyfinger halves, cut side down, into espresso; arrange dipped side down, on top of first layer.

Spread 2 cups cheese mixture evenly over ladyfingers; repeat procedure with remaining ladyfinger halves, espresso and cheese mixture. Place one toothpick in each corner and one in the center of tiramisu (to prevent plastic wrap from sticking to cheese mixture); cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 3 to 8 hours.
Remove toothpicks; sprinkle with cocoa.

title: fried potatoes and zucchini
directions: Mix all together.
Fry in butter until potatoes are done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits except strawberries (may also add other fruit favorites).
Add frozen strawberries 1/2 hour before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Mix milk and sugar together and pour in tube pan.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk, lime peel and juice.
Add food coloring.
Blend until smooth and thick.
Stir in egg yolks and blend well.
Bake in selected pie shell for 15 minutes at 350° and cool.
Top with whipped cream, chocolate slivers and a twist of green lime slice.

title: wonder fudge
directions: Put margarine, chocolate, corn syrup and vanilla into a large saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar.
Add Rice Krispies. Stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 25 squares.

title: some more snot
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and pork sausage.
Melt cheese on low heat in crock-pot.
Add meat mixture and serve warm on bread.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; dry and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Coat in mixture of flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Place in skillet in which shortening has been heated to a moderately hot temperature and fry, turning slices until they are golden brown.

title: grandma jones applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add applesauce, raisins and nuts. Sift together all dry ingredients, then add together with vanilla.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake in 2 tube cake pans (one 9-inch and one 6-inch) or two loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Then add buttermilk and yeast.
Work into flour.
Roll out biscuits on floured board.
Let biscuits rise on pan about 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 450° until golden brown. Serve with honey butter.
May be stored in Tupperware in refrigerator and used later.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mixture in 12x2x12 inch dish.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed. Serve with corn chips.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: piccalilli
directions: Combine all the vegetables and the salt; let stand overnight. In the morning, drain the vegetables, pressing out the juice.
Add the vinegar, sugar and the spices (tied in a bag); bring to a boil and simmer until the vegetables are clear and the syrup is thickened.
Discard the spice bag and seal the piccalilli in hot jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly; when half beaten, add salt and cream of tartar.
Beat stiff.
Fold in sugar, flour and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Bake in moderate oven 50 minutes.
Do not grease tin.
Let little cold water in cake pan.
Turn pan over without drying.
Add batter; use wire beater.

title: italian clam chowder
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender with pepper flakes or Tabasco sauce. Add juice from clams and potato cubes.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini (or celery) and simmer 5 minutes.
Add clams, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Serve garnished with croutons.
Good made ahead.

title: hot corn
directions: Melt margarine in small pan over low heat.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Combine mixture with remaining ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Make a batter of 1/2 cup sugar, milk, baking powder, butter, salt and flour.
Put in a baking dish.
Pour cherries over top, then boiling water or juice.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: good fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice.
Mix soup and milk.
Combine chicken, rice and soup mixture.
Pour into casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Combine yeast and warm water together.
Set aside.
Bring milk to a boil and set off burner.
Add Crisco and sugar.
Let this cool until luke warm.
Add 3 cups flour then yeast mixture. Mix. Add egg.
Add two more cups of flour and mix.
Cover with damp towel and let rise for 45 minutes.
Pour out and kneed until not sticky.
Melt 1 stick butter in bread pan.
Use this to flip rolls in.
Let rise again until pan is full.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.
Put on lettuce leaf in bowl and serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken on medium heat for 1 hour.
Reserve 1 1/4 cups of broth from cooked chicken.
After chicken has cooled, remove from the bone and put in a greased 11 1/2 x 7 x 2-inch casserole dish. Melt one stick of margarine and pour over chicken.
Add one cup of milk to one cup of flour and mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Add 1 1/4 cups of reserved broth to the can of cream of mushroom soup and bring to a boil over medium heat.
After soup comes to a boil, pour over chicken.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 minutes or until golden.

title: cherry jello dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beaten egg whites. Add nuts and pineapple.
Layer the crushed graham crackers, creamed mixture, graham crackers, mixture and partly chilled Jell-O on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Chill thoroughly and serve.

title: lovely leftovers
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion until tender, but not brown. Add meat and stir until blended.
Add chicken broth and thicken with cornstarch.
Add salt and pepper and simmer about 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
To serve, arrange tomato wedges on top.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: onion soup
directions: Let simmer for a few minutes.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown ground round until no longer pink; drain all other ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pepper relish
directions: Put peppers (discard seeds) and peeled onions through food chopper.
Add boiling water to cover; let stand 10 minutes. Drain and discard liquid.
Add remaining ingredients to vegetables.
Boil slowly 15 minutes.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes 6 pints.

title: betty's cavatini
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Boil pasta and drain.
Mix sausage, macaroni, tomato sauce and noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put pepperoni on top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Add cheese to top and bake another 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and margarine to soft ball stage.
Quickly add chips and fluff; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix again. Pour into pan.
Cut and cool.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Melt butter in baking pan; mix in remaining ingredients.
Coat chicken. Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, oil, vanilla and milk together thoroughly. Add flour, salt and cocoa; mix thoroughly.
Drop walnut size on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; place 1/2 large marshmallow on each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 2 minutes.
Remove and cool.
May be frosted if desired.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add taco sauce, beans and tomatoes.
Put in pan.
Mix Jiffy mix by directions on box.
Pour over bean mixture.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° until bread is done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Stir constantly for two minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Heat water and margarine to boil.
Remove from
heat, add flour and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread over bottom and up to halfway to the sides of the pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and oleo. Let stand 15 minutes; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chinese almond sugar cookies(mom's recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg to mixture; beat well.
Add almond extract; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Flour hands and form small balls (about the size of doughnut centers).
Roll balls in sugar; flatten slightly with thumb.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven until edges are slightly browned (10 to 12 minutes).
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Unroll crescent dough and spread on ungreased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, cottage cheese and dressing.
Spread on cooled dough.
Spread vegetables on top.
Chill overnight and cut in squares.
Make a day ahead.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press the crescent rolls out in pan forming one large pie crust.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Mix the softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed, garlic salt and onion.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Top with your favorite diced vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, mushrooms, etc.
Can top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: white peanut butter fudge
directions: Add hot mixture.
Add one cup English walnuts, if desired. Pour into buttered cake pan.

title: bacon topped cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Beat until blended.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Combine bacon, parsley and almonds.
Stir. Roll cheese ball in bacon mixture.
Wrap in wax paper and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter and stir.
Heat to a full, rolling boil; lower heat.
Boil exactly 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in chips and stir to melt chips.
Add flour, vanilla and cracker crumbs.
Mix hard and fast. Mixture will get thick.
Put in well-greased 12 x 8-inch pan.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Whip the cream.
Combine with softened ice cream.
Add lemon juice, Cointreau and rum.
Mix with strawberries which have been sugared.
Serve in parfait glasses.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna oriental
directions: Place celery, onion and butter in 1-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave on full power for 3 minutes or until celery and onion are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients using only 1 cup of chow mein noodles.
Season with salt and pepper, as desired.
Top with remaining chow mein noodles.
Cook in microwave on full power for 6 to 7 minutes or until heated through and temperature of 150° is reached.

title: congo squares
directions: Stir brown sugar and butter over low heat to melt butter. Cool.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans and semi-sweet chips. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: best ever coconut pound cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in prepared tube pan. Cool.

title: snappers crab stew
directions: In a kettle, cook the carrots, celery and the onion in the butter over moderately low heat, stirring, until the vegetables are softened.
Add the flour and cook the roux, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Add milk, cream, bay leaf, black pepper, salt, cayenne, Old Bay seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring the mixture to a boil; simmer and stir for 8 to 10 minutes, or until thickened slightly.
Add crab meat; cook mixture, stirring for 1 minute, and discard the bay leaf.
Makes about 12 cups, 8 to 10 servings.

title: mildred's seafood casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Oil or butter bottom of rectangular dish or pan; cut crusts from bread and line bottom of dish with bread slices.
Saute veggies and combine with salad dressing and fish; spoon this mixture over bread slices.
Combine eggs, milk and soup and pour over all.
Chill overnight or 2 to 3 hours; bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese over top and melt in oven a few extra minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar and salt.
Add yeast, egg and shortening. Mix in 6 1/2 to 7 cups flour.
Refrigerate for up to 1 week. When ready to use, form rolls; cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until done, about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: after ham and cabbage casserole
directions: Cut ham, potatoes and cabbage into small pieces and layer with onions in rectangular baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Cover ingredients with 1/2 of cheese.
Layer can of corn (do not drain). Beat eggs and milk together.
Add Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and green peppers on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and liquid sets, about 30 minutes.

title: mrs. albright's infamous mustard burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix in mustard.
Spoon on toasted buns or bread.
Quick, hot and tasty!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese. Add sugar and peanut butter.
Slowly add milk.
Beat until smooth. Add 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth or creamy.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with extra Cool Whip (chocolate syrup and peanuts, if desired).
Freeze until needed. Defrost in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients with bacon fat and cook, covered, for 20 minutes on simmer.
In a large 3 1/2-quart casserole, mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: mocha coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart airtight container. Makes about 3 1/2 cups mix or 10 to 12 servings.

title: "easy" chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove chicken from bone and return to large pot of broth. Add can of broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook until tender.
Add noodles.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.

title: boston brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Add melted chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 min.
Center will be gooey.
Cool and refrigerate for 1-2 hrs.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or add whole pecans on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients; chill for an hour or so.
Form into ball; roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: macaroni meat loaf
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Gradually add milk and cream.
Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix macaroni with cheese sauce.
Mix together egg, stuffing, beef and remaining salt and pepper.
Spread on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with macaroni mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Sprinkle apricot jello over Cool Whip and mix well.
Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple tidbits.
Add to cool whip and jello mixture.
Add marshmallows and stir well.
Let set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mr. hendershot's peanut brittle candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and stir well.
Cook on high heat until light straw color.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Cook to boil, stirring constantly.
Add butter and soda; stir well and pour on buttered platter at once.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: kissing cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Turn mixer speed to low and gradually add flour until well mixed.
Wrap dough in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator if you prefer to work with a stiffer dough.
Peel foil from chocolate Kisses and shape dough around each Kiss, using about 2 tablespoonfuls for each one.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake in a 375° oven until "set" but not brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Cool and store in airtight container. This recipe will make 4 dozen or more pretty-party cookies that retain the shape of the chocolate Kiss.

title: molded cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries; measure juice and add enough water to make 2 cups.
Heat liquid; dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Cool gelatin until consistency of egg white.
Pour small amount in oiled mold and chill until set.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together; add to other mixture and mix.
Soften the chocolate over water and blend. Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook approximately 45 minutes.
Dip with Fritos.

title: pineapple waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 c. of juice. In a bowl combine first five ingredients. In another bowl combine mayonnaise, yogurt, sugar and the 1/2 c. pineapple juice. Pour over fruit mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate until serving.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cocktail sauce, together.
Form mixture into a ball.
Chill 2 hours.
Pour cocktail sauce over it when ready to serve.
Can be served with crackers (I would recommend Wheatables).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Mix shortening, salt and sugar; add eggs, sifted ingredients, banana pulp and nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in 4 layers in a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle first 3 layers with onion salt, 1 teaspoon flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Sprinkle fourth layer with remaining salt and flour.
Dot with butter.
Pour hot milk over potatoes; bake, covered, 30 minutes, then bake, uncovered, 60 to 70 minutes. Serves 5 to 6.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream margarine, brown sugar (no lumps) and granulated sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal and nuts.
Dough will become very thick.
Form into rolls (about 2 to 2 1/2-inches in diameter).
Chill well.
Cut 1/4-inch thick and bake for 10 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies should be a little soft when removed from oven.
They will become crispier as they cool.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine like predough and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: golden glow punch(serves 25 four ounce servings)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Make pineapple-orange juice as directions state.
Combine jello, water, juices and ginger ale.
Refrigerate until served.

title: shrimp dip (hot or cold)(makes 2 cups)
directions: Blend shrimp soup, cream cheese, sour cream and Worcestershire sauce with mixer.
Add tiny shrimp.
Mix together and serve with crackers.

title: basic trail mix
directions: Mix all together.
Nice change for a snack.

title: salad supreme
directions: Mix jello according to package directions.
Chill.
Drain pineapple; reserve the liquid.
Fold pineapple into jello.
Chill until mixture congeals. Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Blend in softened cream cheese.
Spread on top of jello.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup liquid. Combine sugar, flour, lemon juice and eggs.
Add to juice and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Add chopped pecans and spread over Dream Whip and cream cheese layer.
Chill.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: tomato-basil salad
directions: Slice tomatoes and onion thinly.
Mix with basil.
Pour vinegar over the salad.
Add pepper.
Let marinate at least 1/2 hour or preferably for 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove chicken and debone.
Reserve water and add more water if necessary for boiling spaghetti.
Cook spaghetti until done; drain liquid and discard.

title: seafood kabobs(6 kabobs)
directions: Wrap each piece of seafood in bacon.
Thread pieces on 10-inch skewers as follows:
green pepper, lobster, mushroom, scallop, mushroom, shrimp and green pepper.
Add a cherry tomato to each skewer during the last five minutes of grilling.
Grill 3-inches from coals for 10 to 12 minutes or until done, turning and brushing frequently with marinade.

title: kraut runzes
directions: Cook separately the ground beef and the chopped cabbage. Drain and mix together.
Season with salt and pepper to taste (don't be shy on the salt). Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: pralines
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, mix and cook over low flame the sugar and cream to soft ball stage or 238°.
Turn flame off.
Add vanilla and butter.
Do not stir.
Cool to lukewarm or 110°.
Add pecans and beat until thick and mixture begins to loose its gloss. Drop by tablespoon onto greased dish or waxed paper.
If candy becomes too stiff to drop, heat slightly to dropping consistency. Yields about 30 to 36 pralines.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add all other ingredients. Chill until ready for use.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the flour, sugar, salt and butter until it resembles coarse meal.
Press into 12 x 18-inch baking pan and bake 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and
flour
3 coffee cans.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fill cans half full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool;
slice and serve with butter.

title: treasure chest bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in bowl the sugars and margarine.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Begin and end with dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain.
Mix broccoli, rice and Cheez Whiz. Simmer onion and celery 15 minutes in butter.
Add to broccoli and mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: aunt rose's shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugars; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add chopped nuts. Mix flour, soda and salt; add and mix well.
Divide dough in half. Shape dough in 2 long rolls 2-inches in diameter; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch and place on greased cookie sheet.
Store in airtight container.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put peeled tomatoes through grinder.
Cook the peppers and onions together with tomatoes for 1 to 2 hours, then add spices. Cook all together for about 2 hours very slow, then add spices and sugar and taste.
If needed, add more sugar and spices.
Bottle while very hot.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears, reserve juice.
Add water to pear juice to make 2 cups.
Heat the juice.
Pour over jello and mix well.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Mash pears with cream cheese. Add to jello mixture.
Mix in Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour into serving dish and chill.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Put 1 dill heat and a piece of dill stalk or if you don't have garden dill use about 2 Tbsp. dill seed, pepper, garlic bud and alum in your jar.
Wash cucumbers and pack in jars.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with 1 tablespoon wine; add other ingredients. Cook in oven for 15 minutes at 375°. Serve with Triscuits or other favorite crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Mix macaroni and 2 slices of cheese, then pour into baking dish.
Add milk.
Put pinches of the cheese on top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or starting to get dry.

title: sweet and spicy meatballs
directions: Combine jelly and chili sauce in large pot or crock-pot.
Heat to simmer.
Add meatballs.
(You can brown them in the oven at 400° for 10 minutes first if you prefer.)
Simmer for at least 2 hours on medium heat.
If you use crock-pot, use low setting for 4 to 6 hours.

title: elegant crab
directions: Cube bread.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Gently fold in cubes and crabmeat.
Spoon mixture into baking dish (oblong) and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with white sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked sea trout
directions: Clean trout and pat dry with paper towels to absorb excess water.
Place trout (skin side down) in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Season fish with salt, pepper, oregano and lemon juice (season for own taste).
Spread a thin coating of mayonnaise on top of fish.
Sprinkle a layer of Parmesan cheese on top.

title: buttered spinach fettuccine
directions: Bring 4 quarts of water to a boil.
Add the fettuccine and simmer until just done.
Drain.
Pour the pasta back into the pot. Add the butter, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour into warm bowl and serve.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage coarser than for kraut.
Put in a saucepan; add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook cabbage until tender.
Add rolled crackers and oleo to drained cabbage.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar. Pour mixture into baking dish; add milk to cabbage mixture.
Dot with cheese on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into a casserole dish.

title: portuguese kale soup (couvres)
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Drain in the morning. Add onion, sausage, kale, salt, vinegar and 9 cups water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes and 1 cup water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine artichoke hearts, chopped chili peppers, cheese and mayonnaise.
Turn mixture into 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Cook beans for 30 minutes.
If fresh, add a small amount of salt (to taste).

title: peanut butter cups
directions: You will also need a muffin tin with shallow cups.

title: chilled strawberry soup
directions: Puree strawberries in food processor or blender.
Strain into a saucepan; add orange juice.
In a small bowl, mix tapioca with 4 tablespoons of pureed strawberry mixture.
Add to saucepan with allspice and cinnamon.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to boil.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Pour into large bowl.
Add sugar, lemon peel, lemon juice and buttermilk; blend well.
Cover; chill at least 8 hours.
Taste; add more lemon flavoring, if needed.
Serve with fresh berry or lemon slice. Serves 6.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Shape into 4 dozen small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Brown in moderate oven (375°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut up orange slices.
Beat eggs; add sugar and beat.
Mix flour with nuts and candy, then add to eggs and sugar.
Bake in a shallow loaf pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch) at 325° until brown.
Cut in squares.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: corn flake kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating.
Gently fold in remaining ingredients.
Barely mix together.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Makes 30 small kisses.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Melt chocolate morsels in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Add peanuts to melted chocolate and stir to coat. Turn out on waxed paper, spreading so that peanuts are separated as much as possible.
Allow to cool completely.

title: sausage bread
directions: Cook sausage with bell pepper and onion. Drain grease well. Line bottom of Bundt pan with biscuits. Cover with half of the cooked mixture. Cover with cheese. Repeat. Cover with foil and cook 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Remove foil and cook additional 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand until mixed well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place on bottom of baking dish. Spread cranberry sauce over apples.
Combine other ingredients and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: quickie apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients and eggs and apples beaten together with dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Chill one hour.
Form 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. After cool, roll in powdered sugar.
Double recipe makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips; roll dough into 1-inch balls.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients.
Stir until well blended in small saucepan.
Boil until spins thread, then beat in egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup melted butter, onion soup, sour cream and cheese.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Crush corn flakes and stir in the remaining butter.
Sprinkle on the potato mixture and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cheese.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Spread batter in loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool 10 more minutes.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti bolognese
directions: Fry meat until brown.
In separate pan, fry mushrooms, garlic and onions in the butter.
Drain off fat from both pans and join together.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Add all other ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cook over medium heat while spaghetti is cooking.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in Miracle Whip and sugar.
Add fruit and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into loaf pan (8 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch).
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Take from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into slices.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli in small pieces.
Fry bacon crisp; crumble over broccoli.
Shred cheese.
Mix with broccoli and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli, bacon and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Serve chilled.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix in saucepan the cocoa, 1 cup sugar, flour, egg yolks and milk; cook until thick.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: fish creole*
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook until tender.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Place fish in baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Lightly sprinkle with salt, pepper and red pepper. Drizzle 1 tablespoon lemon juice over fish.
Broil until light brown and fork-tender.
Spoon vegetable sauce over fish.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soup and onion.
Cut chicken in pieces.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put broccoli on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour soup mixture over that.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until soft and drain.
Fry onion in margarine until transparent.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 1/2-quart casserole pan at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add jalapeno pepper and cook in microwave 5 minutes.
Add green chilies, Ro-Tel and cheese until melted.
Finally add cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: basic herb vinaigrette
directions: Combine in a blender and let stand at room temperature for several hours to allow the flavors to mellow.
Store covered in the refrigerator, but return to room temperature before using. Makes 4 cups.
Use this in Pasta Salad A La Greque.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces and rub with salt, pepper and some paprika.
Place in a bowl and add garlic, white wine, lemon juice and a little sugar.
Toss well and marinate in the refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw. Drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, biscuit mix, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian bean soup
directions: Cut ham in small pieces. Dice celery. Thinly slice carrots. Chop onions. Dice zucchini. Remove 1 cup of white kidney beans and mash with fork. In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, add olive oil, ham, celery, carrots, onion, zucchini, basil and pepper until vegetables are tender (about 15 minutes). Stir in stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, spinach, white mashed beans and 2 cups of water. Using spoon to break up tomatoes, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes to blend flavors. Stir in remaining beans. Heat through.

title: old fashioned chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken with onion, herbs and spices.
When chicken is tender, remove from broth and debone.
Return to broth and add potatoes, carrots, corn, green beans, tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Good with cornbread!

title: ricotta cake
directions: Make Duncan Hines butter cake according to the directions and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl. Refrigerate.
Use jello dry.

title: liza's lentil soup
directions: Sort like beans.
Wash good and cook as you would a pot of beans.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and onion, then add tomatoes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: spiced hot apple drink
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a well greased casserole dish. I use a 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 12-inch dish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Prepare cornmeal as directed on package.
Put corn in one corn meal mix.
Pour in greased large skillet or pan.
Place cooked meat on top.
Place cut vegetables on top of meat.
Spread cheese on top.
Place sliced cheese on top of shredded cheese.
Pour second corn meal mix on top of cheese and cook until done, about 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin coconut bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in fridge overnight. Yum!
So simple, but so good!

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter, mixing well.
Shape into 4 flat patties.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute patties on both sides until golden brown and heated through.
Serve with white sauce and peas.

title: spiced tea
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 30 minutes.
Take spices out; put in pitcher.
Good on a cold day.

title: rhonda's favorite cabbage roll
directions: Core cabbage and place in boiling water so leaves will peel and roll easily.
Peel off leaves as needed with tongs or fork. Mix beef, onion, Rice-A-Roni and salt and pepper to taste in a large bowl.
Roll 2-inch balls in each leaf.
Rice will expand them.
Place tightly together in a baking pan.
Spread sauerkraut over them and pour on tomato juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: christmas waldorf salad
directions: Blend cream cheese and canned milk until smooth.
Dissolve jello in liquid and add sugar, vinegar, lemon and salt.
When partly congealed, add cheese and milk, blend with last 4 ingredients.
Mold in desired shape.

title: tasty veggie spirelli salad
directions: Combine the onion and vinegar and let it stand for a few minutes.
Then add the mayonnaise, salt, pepper, and paprika and mix well.
Mix the veggie spirelli, tomatoes, green pepper, and olives in
a large salad bowl; and pour the mayonnaise mixture over all.
Toss lightly.
Chill the salad for several hours before serving.
When serving, garnish with the egg slices and parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Bottom Layer:
Beat together the cream cheese, sour cream, taco sauce and taco seasoning.
The rest of the ingredients get layered, except tortilla chips.
Refrigerate until serving.
Scoop with tortilla chips.

title: 5 cheese lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
In large pan, add ground beef, 2 cans of tomato sauce, plus 1 can of water, onions, oregano and garlic.
Let cook until thick; set aside.
Cook noodles.

title: grape salad
directions: Layer grapes, sour cream and then brown sugar.
Refrigerate. Before serving, add pecans and stir gently until grapes are coated.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, hull and drain berries.
Slice and place in cool crust. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes longer and add jello, stirring until jello dissolves. Pour over strawberries while hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening thoroughly; gradually add sugar.
Add beaten eggs and peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt several times. Add gradually; mix well.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on aluminum cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Fry onion, sausage and hamburger meat together in a small amount of oil until meat is brown and onion is soft.
Add tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Then spoon sauce onto rolls and roll up. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a simmer.
Strain and serve lukewarm to hot.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook until done.
Season with salt, pepper, 1/2 cup sugar, Worcestershire sauce and parsley.
Makes 12 quarts.

title: souperburger sandwiches
directions: In a medium skillet over medium high heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat. Pour off fat. Add soup, mustard and pepper. Reduce heat to low and heat through. Divide meat mixture among buns.

title: apple crisp
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place sliced apples in pan.
Mix together rest of the ingredients and place over top of apples. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and pour into ungreased Pyrex pan.
No other pan will do. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: breast of chicken with chanterelles(or ordinary fresh mushrooms)
directions: Lightly dredge chicken in flour, salt and paprika.
Melt butter and saute 5 minutes.
Turn only once.
Add chanterelles (or mushrooms) and cook 1 minute.
Add flour (the 2 tablespoons); cook 1 minute.
Add sherry and cream.
Cook until thickened.
Add ham. Heat and serve.
(Run under broiler to brown.)
Serves 4.

title: surprise dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with chips, crackers, bread or as a salad dressing.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef well and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until cheese is melted.
Keep on warming tray until serving time or make dip immediately before serving.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: banana split
directions: Mix together the graham cracker crumbs, melted margarine and sugar and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Following package directions, mix the 2 packages instant vanilla pudding and place on crust.
Top with the bananas (sliced thick and pressed into pudding), pineapple and strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Best served same day.

title: sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: In a 4-cup bowl, mix dry milk and water until smooth. Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Microwave on High 30 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds until heated thoroughly, not boiling. Makes 1 1/3 cups (equivalent of one 14 ounce can).

title: death by chocolate
directions: In a trifle bowl layer brownies, then pudding, then Heath bars, then Cool Whip.
Repeat layers ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix eggs, cold water and sugar in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix shortening, margarine and boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix all together in large bowl; add flour and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready, knead and roll out on floured board.
Cut out with biscuit cutter. Fold in half and dip in margarine.
Put on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring water, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Stuff jars with cucumbers, onions, grapes and grape leaves, peppers, garlic and dill.
Pour brine in jars.
Seal jars and put in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon; reserve grease.
Dry bacon and crumble.
Fry onions in bacon grease.
Add in sugar, salt, pepper, flour, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add in potatoes and bacon. Toss and add in celery seed and parsley.
Let stand and slightly cool.
Add in eggs and green pepper.
Serve warm.

title: chili con carne with beans
directions: Cook meat and onion. Drain. Add chili powder and cumin. Stir well. Add tomato sauce and broth. Cook, stirring often, 20 minutes. Add cocoa, oregano and beans. Heat through. Serve with a little cheese. Enjoy. Serves 6 to 8.

title: individual cream cheese balls
directions: If desired for variations, 1/4 cup of Roquefort cheese may be added.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 40 to 45 minutes.

title: choco chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine or butter, brown sugar and granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt gradually mixing until well blended.
Stir in uncooked oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Remove to wire cooling rack; cool completely.
Store in covered container.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chicken strata
directions: Take 4 slices of bread, salt, pepper, butter and cube.
Set aside.
Cube the remaining 2 pieces and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Combine chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise in a bowl. Spoon onto the bread in pan.
Take the buttered bread cubes and put on top of mixture. Combine eggs and milk; pour over casserole.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup over top. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mussels in sauce
directions: In large saucepot, combine oil, garlic and onions.
Saute until onions are transparent.
Add tomatoes and simmer about 45 minutes.
Add mussels, parsley, red pepper and wine.
Simmer until all mussels are open (about 40 minutes).
Serve over linguini.

title: little ham loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix ham, pork, 1/2 cup of reserved pineapple syrup, bread crumbs, eggs, onion and parsley.
Divide mixture into 6 parts; shape into loaves. Place in ungreased rectangular dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Top each with 3 pineapple chunks, pressing lightly into loaves.

title: heavenly cranberry relish
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of microwave safe dish.
Layer chili with beans on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes.
Remove and stir. Serve with nacho chips.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water and cook over low heat until thick, about 10 minutes, then add nuts and cool.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice.
Add sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Mix and refrigerate, stirring at least once a day until all sugar is dissolved.
Ready to use in a few days.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix yogurt and pudding mix in a bowl; stir in pineapple and extracts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Delicious with fruits.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the eggs in a large mixing bowl with an electric mixer until frothy, then stir in the corn and onion with a wooden spoon.
Mix the flour, salt, sugar, cayenne and nutmeg to taste in a small bowl and add to the corn mixture, stirring constantly.
Add the butter and half and half and stir well.

Pour the mixture into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish; place dish in a large roasting pan; place pan in the oven and pour enough boiling water into pan to come one-quarter up the sides of the baking dish.
Bake pudding for 15 minutes; stir gently with a fork to distribute corn as evenly as possible.
Bake 30 minutes more or until top is golden and a knife inserted into the center emerges clean.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in large bowl the sour cream, chicken soup, onion and cheese.
Mix well and stir in potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in 9 x 13 pan.
Before baking, top with melted oleo and corn flakes; sprinkle over potatoes and dribble the melted oleo over them.
Makes a nice topping.

title: homemade potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water (barely).
Boil until done.
Leave water; add milk and butter.
Simmer.

title: enchiladas santa fe style
directions: In a 6-quart pot, brown hamburger meat with onion.
Add 1 tablespoon flour; stir in meat until brown.
Add 4 quarts of water.
Add 4 tablespoons of chili powder, chopped garlic, 1 teaspoon oregano, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon cumin.
Stir until chili has dissolved in water.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: heavenly cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar, sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Add flour; mix well.
Cut 6 caramels into chip-size pieces. Add caramel chips, chocolate chips and nuts to mixture; stir. Spread dough into an 8 x 12-inch ungreased baking dish.
Press remaining whole caramels into cookie dough.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn oven off and let stand until center of dough is done.
Take out of oven, let cool for a few minutes and then cut into bars.

title: moussaka (greek)(party dish)
directions: Peel eggplant, cut crosswise in 1/4-inch slices and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Arrange in stacks.
Place heavy plate on top. Let stand to drain.

title: cheesy creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a slow cooker and mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until cheese is melted.
Stir well before serving.

title: sweetened condensed milk #2
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, water and butter or margarine. Heat until mixture boils, stirring. Add powdered milk and stir until mixture is smooth. Refrigerate until needed. Makes 1 cup.

title: two-crust chicken pie
