directions: Microwave peas and carrots using package directions.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken broth, milk, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and peas and carrots.
Cook until heated through.
Spoon into pastry-lined pie plate.
Top with remaining pastry.
Trim and seal edge; cut vents.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: easy sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Heat cheese over low heat, stirring often.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips or over burgers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use electric mixer and beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until knife stuck in the middle comes out clean.

title: raisin-pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add pumpkin, salt and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(I always double recipe and freeze cookies for later.)

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions (medium heat) in butter just until clear.
Layer onions, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Ritz crackers (1/2 of each).
Repeat layers with other half of the ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place sauerkraut in an 8 x 8 Pyrex dish.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.

title: marshmallow mandarin topping
directions: Chop mandarins into small pieces, mix in 1 tablespoon of the reserved syrup and the marshmallow cream.
This is great served over pound cake or sponge cake.

title: fried gar
directions: Clean animal and cut up.
Soak in salt water 3 hours, drain. Dip meat in melted butter, then in crushed cornflakes.
Brown in hot fat or oil; reduce heat.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Salt and pepper.

title: guatemalan 7 layer dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 F. In a medium bowl, combine refried beans, black beans, and taco seasoning, mix. Spread bean mixture in an ungreased 8 inch square covered baking dish. Spread sour cream over bean mixture. Top with salsa, chiles, jalapenos, and cheese, cover dish. Bake for 20 minutes, uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and dip is starting to bubble up. Garnish with green onions. Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 10.

title: cocoa bars
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
If desired, can add nuts. Spread in rectangular pan.
Frost and cut into squares.

title: carrot meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan at 350° for one hour or until baked through; drain fat from pan.
Let stand 10 minutes, turn onto hot platter and slice.
Serves 6.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion, salt, sugar. Beat eggs, add to squash. Add melted butter, add flour. Drop by tbsp. on oiled griddle. Brown on both sides. Serve immediately.

title: cheese filled pears
directions: Drain pears;
reserve
juice
and
set	aside.	Combine cream cheese and	honey.	Beat
until blended.
Fill pears 1/2 full with cream cheese mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs on
top.
Add some juice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves
6 to 8.
Great as a side dish with ham or served as a dish for brunch.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Slice zucchini, squash and onion.
Place in a skillet with enough olive oil to cover the bottom of the pan.
Saute until almost tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Dice 1 large fresh tomato and add to mixture, stirring until tender.

title: green beans lyonnaise
directions: Cook green beans in boiling water until tender.
Drain and pat dry on paper toweling.
In skillet, saute onions in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add green beans, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley and lemon juice.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spread 1 cup sour cream.
In 2-quart saucepan with fork, flake chicken; add 1/2 cup sour cream, mushrooms and next 6 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until heated through.
Along center line of tortilla, spread 1/4 cup chicken mixture; fold sides over filling and place, seam side down, in sour cream in pan; repeat.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread enchiladas with remaining sour cream, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serves 6.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with chips or crackers.

title: chicken breast and stuffing
directions: Layer in 13x9-inch pan in order as listed, sprinkle sparingly with stuffing.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried fresh peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place peaches in 1 quart baking dish. In small sauce pan mix orange juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, curry powder and ginger. Stirring over medium-low heat, bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute or until thickened. Stir in butter and pour over fruit. Sprinkle coconut on top. Bake 25-30 minutes or until coconut is lightly toasted and fruit is bubbly.

title: corned beef pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add onion, brown lightly.
Stir in flour gradually; blend smooth.
Add stewed tomatoes slowly. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Stir in corned beef.
Set aside to cool slightly while making pastry for pie.
Make regular pie crust (2).
Put filling in pie crust, cover with second crust and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together all soups, sour cream and shredded Cheddar cheese in crock-pot.
Heat until hot.
Serve with nacho chips and jalapenos.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Melt margarine, cream cheese and milk together in saucepan. Add corn and chilies to cream mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta fasuel
directions: Fry hamburg, onion and garlic in oil.
Add paste, lentils and 5 paste cans of water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Mix with elbow or pasta of your choice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese get soft first.
Add Meat Magic and mix well into the cream cheese.
Form into a ball and roll the cream cheese ball into nuts or chopped almonds.
Serve on crackers.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until nearly done.
Place in bottom of ovenproof dish.
Add onions, salt and pepper to taste, margarine and soup. Top with cheese.
Cook in oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Add grated cheese to softened margarine. Sift flour and pepper together. Then add to cheese and margarine mixture. Add Rice Krispies. Roll into small balls and mash with a fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy p-nut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix sugar, brown sugar, margarine or butter, vanilla and peanut butter until creamy, then add 1/2 the flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt; blend. Then add rest of flour until stiff. Spoon out by teaspoonfuls at 2-inches apart; flatten gently with a fork. Bake 7 to 12 minutes (cookies burn easy) or until golden brown around edges.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all of the above together and cook till thick and clear. Beat 3 egg yolks slightly and blend into hot mixture a little at a time.
Stir constantly- add juice and grated rind of lemon add 3 tsp. butter.
Pour into pie shell. and top with meringue.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in bottom of casserole dish.
Add chicken, rice and seasoning mix and onion soup mix (dry).
Add about 4 cups of chicken broth and pour the rest of the butter over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender at 350°.
Stir occasionally and add more broth if needed.

title: chicken divan
directions: In a large casserole, greased with butter, lay broccoli on bottom, then lay chicken on top.
Mix mayonnaise, both cans of soup and lemon juice well.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs mixed with melted butter on top. Can sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aloha carrots
directions: Combine carrots, water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook over medium heat about 10 to 12 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir in brown sugar, crushed pineapple and butter.
Cook additional 3 to 5 minutes; watch to avoid sticking. Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in glass mixing bowl in microwave for 1 minute and 40 seconds.
Lay out 2 large pieces of plastic wrap on counter (cross-shaped, one piece on top of other).
Take 7 whole pieces of beef out of package and lay 5 pieces in circle on plastic wrap with room in middle for cream cheese mixture.
Save 2 pieces for top of cheeseball.
Blend with mixer the cream cheese, remaining beef, chopped up into small pieces, Accent, freeze dried chives and garlic.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook until done.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together in a bowl.
Put in a pan butter, cocoa, water and salt.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour; stir well.
Add milk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in an 18 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: oven chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees (Hot).
Melt butter in oblong cake pan in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Turn chicken over in melted butter to coat.
Place chicken skin side down in baking pan allowing spaces between pieces.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and paprika.
Bake chicken 10 to 15 minutes longer or until tender.

title: skillet tomatoes
directions: Cook tomatoes in butter in skillet, cut side down, for about 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes. Sinmer 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheeses; add onion salt, garlic salt, paprika and cayenne pepper to taste.
Stir in 3/4 cups pecans; mix thoroughly.
Line small mixing bowl with Saran Wrap and press mixture into it. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Roll in 3/4 cups pecans before serving.

title: pat's pumpkin bars
directions: Mix well.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Combine brown sugar and flour; stir in margarine until light and crumbly.
Press mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of two loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar in a large bowl. Add eggs and water.
Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla and cloves. Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 1 hour. Cool completely before slicing.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.
Beat the eggs into the milk.
Dip rings first into milk, then the flour, then back into the milk, then into the cracker meal.
Freeze one layer at a time on a cookie sheet.
Separate the layers with wax paper.
Fry them in hot shortening while they are still frozen.

title: hamburg-potato casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain fat.
Add soup, milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire and let simmer.
Slice potatoes thin. Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, then layer potatoes, alternating with beef sauce mix.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: church windows
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter and chocolate chips over low heat; stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Cool 15 minutes but do not let it harden.
Fold in marshmallows and stir until well coated. Spoon half of mixture lengthwise down center of 12-inch piece of wax paper.
Shape into 12 x 2-inch log and place at one end of wax paper.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut over remainder of wax paper. Roll log over coconut evenly coating outside of log.
Wrap firmly in wax paper folding edges firmly.
Repeat other half until firm for 2 hours or overnight.
Unwrap and cut into 1/4-inch slices. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: Mix together salad dressing and sugar until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread cubes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with
sausage
and
cheese.
Combine
milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over other.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Cook rice and then add to ground chuck, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix, then make in balls. Cook.
Pour grease off and add the tomato soup.
Rinse out can with a little water and heat it. I cook all this in a microwave.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Place 1 layer of biscuits into greased tube or Bundt pan; sprinkle with nuts.
Add 2 more layers of biscuits and nuts. Melt brown sugar and butter; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over layers of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Eat it by pulling apart with fingers.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy, then add the egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate and pecans.
Drop 2 rounded measuring tablespoons about 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy and 11 to 13 minutes for crisp.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Mix glaze and strawberries together.
Spread on cake. Top with Cool Whip (very good).

title: gone all day stew
directions: Cut chuck into 1-inch pieces.
Cut carrots and celery into 1-inch pieces and potatoes into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Mix first 3 ingredients and add to all other ingredients in a covered roasting pan.
Bake covered 4 to 5 hours at 275°.
Can be served over noodles or with toasted French bread.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 311 calories, 8 gr fat.

title: green cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thaw and chop frozen broccoli.
Add butter, cornbread mix, cottage cheese and egg.
Bake in a skillet or square pan until done.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour in greased casserole dish, bake for 45 minutes.

title: cherry fruit squares
directions: Cream the softened margarine and sugar.
Add the vanilla. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then stir in the sifted flour. Add nuts last.
Spread 3/4 of the batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
cover with the cherry pie filling.
Drop the remaining batter by spoonfuls on top and spread it around as best you can. (The cherries should show through a bit.)
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut into little bars.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if you like.

title: indian relish
directions: Run vegetables through food chopper.
Place in a large bowl or container.
Mix in salt and let stand overnight.
Next day, place in a large canner or kettle.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Mix and cook until vegetables are tender.
Pack in canning jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute potatoes, carrots, green pepper and onion in butter in 3-quart saucepan for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover.
Simmer 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add salmon.
Heat to serving temperature over low heat.
Makes 9 cups.

title: crab special
directions: Place cream cheese on serving plate. Pour over enough cocktail sauce to cover. Sprinkle with 1/2 can crabmeat.
When cheese is about half gone, cover again with cocktail sauce and remaining crabmeat. Serve with cheese or butter knife.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Pop open all of biscuits; roll out slightly to wrap around hot dog.
Bake in a 425° oven for approximately 10 minutes (or until brown).

title: german potato salad
directions: In the bacon fat fry onion; blend in flour, sugar, celery seed and salt.
Cook until smooth.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook until smooth, 1 minute.
Mix with warm potatoes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole, layer tomatoes, bread mixture and cheese.
End with a sprinkle of bread crumbs and cheese.
Drizzle with oil.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove cover for the last 10 minutes.
Garnish with tomatoes and basil if desired.

title: boiled custard with berries
directions: Heat milk to scalding; do not boil.
While it is heating, in another bowl, break eggs.
Mix up completely; add sugar.
Spoon some of the heated milk into the eggs and stir well to get them a little warm.
Add egg mix to the hot milk very slowly, stirring all the time.

title: large chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender and take off bones.
Cook noodles in broth. Cook carrot and celery until tender.
Mix all ingredients. Pour into a large baking dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Place diced celery and onions into large shallow pan that will accommodate brisket.
Lay brisket on top.
Combine Coke, barbecue sauce, catsup and water and pour over brisket.
Roast, covered, 3 hours at 325°, watching level of liquid.

title: crackling cornbread(50 years or older)
directions: Mix flour, meal and sugar.
Now add egg and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cracklings; mix well.
Bake in well-oiled skillet or pan.
Bake at 450° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: anything curry(spicy hot!)
directions: Mix all the spices together in a large bowl.
Blend well. Pour vinegar, lime juice and enough water to make a thick paste. Set aside.
Cook onions, peppers, jalapeno and ginger root in oils until soft.
Add tomatoes and cook down.

title: bacon sticks(microwave recipe)
directions: Wrap bacon around bread sticks (barber pole fashion). Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Place on paper plate and paper towel to absorb fat.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Place sticks in a mug or vase to serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Parboil broccoli in 1/2 cup boiling salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain well.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice and half the cheese.

title: stuffed ground beef rolls
directions: Blend ground beef, egg, salt, pepper, bread crumbs and water; mixture will be moist.
Roll in 20-inch long wax paper.
Form a 4-inch wide strip of the meat the length of the wax paper.

title: jane spencer's microwaved potatoes
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Layer potatoes, peppers, onion, salt and pepper.
Repeat until at top of dish.
Dot with oleo, if desired.
Seal with saran wrap.
Microwave on high 5 minutes. Stir.
Microwave on high 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk together.
Then fold in other ingredients.

title: beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Turn into 1 qt. casserole dish.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix beef, cheese, olives and horseradish.
Shape into a ball. Pat on crushed potato chips.
Chill.

title: apple brunch sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into tubular pan.
Place on drip pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loosen from pan with knife.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add Cool Whip. Crumble entire package of Oreos in blender.
Layer one layer of Oreos on bottom of clay pot or dish, then a layer of cream cheese mixture, then a layer of cookies.
Repeat until mixtures are gone. Be sure to leave enough cookie mixture to cover top of cake to look like dirt.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook shrimp for 8 minutes in crab boil.
Clean, arrange in a greased casserole and pour the following sauce over the shrimp.

title: lime cottage gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water, then add 8 ice cubes and stir until cubes melt.
Add remainder in this order: mayonnaise and evaporated milk.
Combine fruit, cottage cheese and horseradish. Mix and pour in a mold and chill well.

title: jo's chess cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Pour in an oblong pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 3 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over cake mix mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt. Soak yeast in cold water for 5 minutes. Add to shortening-sugar mixture. Add eggs and stir. Gradually stir in flour and stir until smooth and elastic.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk. Refrigerate. Can be used after 4 hours from mixing time.

title: ruby apple salad
directions: In large bowl, stir gelatin and candies in boiling water until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 1-quart serving bowl.
Chill until firm, at least 4 hours.

title: lavonne's kraut 'n sausage
directions: Rinse the sauerkraut well.
Drain.
Layer the sauerkraut, onion, brown sugar, bay leaves and smoked sausage in a large crock-pot.
Make several layers.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: egg pancakes
directions: Beat eggs with sour cream.
Add flour and salt and stir until smooth.
(Batter should be consistency of thick cream.)
Melt 1 teaspoon of butter in skillet on high heat.
When hot, turn to medium.
Pour in enough batter (2 or 3 tablespoons) to cover bottom of skillet, tilting pan to spread batter in a thin layer. Brown pancakes on one side (about 1 minute); turn and brown on the other side.
Roll up pancakes and put aside.
Heat maple syrup in skillet.
Add butter and let it melt.
After all pancakes are done, place in syrup-butter mixture to reheat.
Makes 8 or 9 (8-inch) pancakes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.
Serve immediately with chips or crackers.

title: irish soda bread with sour cream
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add raisins and caraway seed.
Blend eggs and sour cream in a small bowl.
Fold into flour mixture until lightly blended. Spoon mixture into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Let set for a few minutes, then turn out onto rack to cool.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Place chicken in a baking pan.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Marinate for 2 hours, turning in 1 hour to be sure to coat chicken evenly.

title: cream gravy
directions: Pour drippings into roasting pan or skillet.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add pint of half and half slowly with bouillon.
Return pan to heat, stirring and scraping all brown bits from pan.
Continue stirring until mixture thickens.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in a dish.
Put about 1/2 cup warm water into yeast and sugar mixture.
Stir and let set until you have flour, etc. ready.

title: crunchy hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together, except cheese.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be served over patty shells.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Parboil chicken and remove bones.
Lay on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with broccoli.
Pour all liquids (mixed together) over the top.
Sprinkle stuffing mix.
Cover with cheese.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add salt and baking soda to flour. Add and mix well to sugar and eggs mix; blend in bananas and nuts. Pour into loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 275° or 300° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Spray 9 x 13 x 2 baking pan with Pam. Peel and quarter apples. Unroll crescent rolls and separate into single triangles. Sprinkle each triangle with cinnamon mixture. Place one quarter of apple on roll and wrap roll around apple, totally covering apple. Place face down in baking pan. Do all apples until complete.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage.	Separate
crescent
dough into 8 triangles. Place triangles with
elongated points toward center in a greased, 12-inch pizza pan.	Press
bottom and sides to form a crust;
seal perforations.
Bake
at
for 5 minutes on lower oven rack. Remove;
crust
will
be puffy.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: muddy buddies(great for kids to make)
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and magarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour mixture over cereal, stirring until pieces are evenly covered.
Pour cereal mixture into resealable plastic bag with powdered sugar.
Seal securely and shake until all pieces are well coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground chuck with onion.
Drain. Add spaghetti sauce to meat and put in casserole dish.
Mix together Mozzarella cheese and sour cream.
Spread over ground beef.
Place crescent rolls over mixture.
Melt butter and add Parmesan cheese.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to the creamed mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts, chocolate chips and apples until evenly distributed.
Grease and flour a 10-inch loose bottom tube pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes at 325°.

title: texas tornado cake
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, fruit cocktail, including juice, baking soda and flour. Pour into lightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: tasty potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and 1 cup of milk and flavoring.
Grate potatoes into remaining 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add coconut and mix remaining ingredients with the milk and potato mixture.
Pour into a greased glass baking dish.
Add melted oleo and cook in slow oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with marshmallows and return to oven until browned.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large quart size jar.
Add onion, lemon juice, vinegar, catsup, oil and garlic bud.
Pour into smaller bottles if desired.
Shake well before using.

title: oyster stew
directions: Pour all ingredients into large pot.
Cook on high, stirring occasionally until butter is melted.
After bringing to a boil, take pot off burner; wait 1 to 2 minutes and replace on burner. Bring to a second boil.
Serve with crackers or oyster stew crackers.

title: swedish pot roast
directions: Combine spices and rub into meat.
Brown meat on all sides in shortening. Put meat in roasting pan and cover with onions and garlic.
Mix brown sugar, wine and water together and pour over meat.
Add bay leaves and bake, covered, at 350°
for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: You will need double boiler or double stacked saucepans, toothpicks and wax paper.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour and bananas.
Stir in salt, vanilla and baking soda until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky road pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat oleo until softened.
Add sugar and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Slowly add in flour.
Beat well.
Spread dough evenly in an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake about 12 minutes or until golden.
Sprinkle walnuts, marshmallows, chocolate and peanut butter chips on top of hot crust.
Return to oven.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are golden.
Cool in pan.
Makes about 32 pieces.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together thoroughly.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
A little milk can be added if this is too thick.
Fry on hot griddle until browned on each side.
Yield: 14 to 16 pancakes.

title: old fashion beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture. Melt shortening in large skillet; brown meat thoroughly.
Add water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Stir in remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.

title: icebox biscuits
directions: Scald buttermilk, cool and add yeast.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Work 1 cup shortening into dry sifted ingredients. Add buttermilk/yeast and mix thoroughly.
This dough will be soft. Cover dough and put in refrigerator.
Pinch off amount of dough you need.
When ready to use, roll on floured board and make into biscuits.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
It isn't necessary to let rise after you make into biscuits, but makes lighter biscuit.

title: stir-fry dinner
directions: You will need a long-handled spoon, wok and cover.

title: nut rolls
directions: Sift flour, sprinkle yeast and salt; add lard.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix together well with hands.
Knead slowly for 5 minutes; kneading makes them flaky.
Shape dough into 4 balls and wrap in damp cloth.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 1 1/2 hours.
Take one ball at a time and roll (on sugar) to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut dough into 2 inch squares.
Put a large teaspoonful of mixture on each square and pinch opposite corners together over filling. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Place chunks of chicken in a large kettle with the broth from the chicken.
Add more broth as needed (canned variety or bouillon cubes and water).
Add corn, potatoes and celery; bring to a boil. Add noodles and cook until done (noodles and potatoes), between 15 to 30 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix well.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: toffee crunch
directions: Butter cookie sheet and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter, water, and syrup.
Cook over med-low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches hard crack stage (about 300° on candy thermometer), about 30 minutes.
Stir in half of almonds. Pour mixture into prepared cookie sheet.
Immediately spread to 1/4 inch thickness.
Sprinkle with chocolate.
Let stand 1 minutes. Spread evenly to cover hot candy.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds before chocolate sets.
Refrigerate until candy has cooled completely.
Break into pieces.
Store in air-tight container.

title: kim's hot pepper jelly
directions: Put all peppers in the blender on fine.
Combine all ingredients, except the pectin.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add pectin and stir well.
Let stand for 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour into small jars and seal.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: beef and rice florentine
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil, leaving bite-size chunks.
Push meat to side of pan.
Add spinach, water, tomato, salt and oregano.
Break up spinach and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp rounds
directions: Cut small rounds of thin white bread with 1 to 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Butter one side of bread; spread other side with Durkee sauce.
Put into large frying pan.
Top sauce with small canned shrimp or fresh cleaned shrimp (cooked).
Top with another tiny dab of Durkee sauce and tiny parsley leaf.
Can refrigerate until ready to cook or fry until golden brown on bottom.
Serve immediately after heating.

title: four bean salad
directions: Chill thoroughly, preferably overnight.

title: sugar free sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat to blend about 2 minutes. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peach trifle
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water; mix well. Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip and 1 tablespoon orange juice.
Place 1/2 of cake pieces in 2-quart bowl or trifle dish.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons orange juice.
Top with half of peaches and 1/2 pudding mixture.
Repeat layering with cake, orange juice, peaches and pudding.
Garnish with nuts.
Refrigerate.
Works well with strawberries.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve pineapple, sugar and jello together (heat until dissolved).
Cool.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onion;
drain
grease.
Add taco seasoning. Put in greased
10-inch
pie plate.
Sprinkle with green chilies. Mix milk, beaten eggs and Bisquick.
Pour over meat. Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more.
Let
cool 5 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium size bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Turn into pie crust.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg whites (at room temperature) with cream of tartar and salt until foamy; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of filling, sealing carefully to edge of crust.
Place filled pie on a cookie sheet in oven and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool; chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop onions and peppers fine.
Combine with cabbage and tomatoes; mix with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well. Combine sugar, spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boiling point and simmer 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer to consistency desired.
Remove spice bag.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cream cheese and clams
directions: Spread on rye rounds and put under broiler.

title: date and nut loaf bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, soak dates in boiling water.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together oil, eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with crushed dates and water until mixture is well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour; cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until browned (drain).
Set aside. Separate dough in 8 triangles arranged on ungreased 12-inch pan. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over filling. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Pizza should have sides so it won't run.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg, molasses and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 8 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: simple apple dumplings
directions: Unroll crescent dough and separate into 8 triangles. Roll up 1 apple wedge in each triangle. Pinch edges to seal. Place in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: green apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into prepared pie shell, sprinkle with cinnamon, top with pie crust, cut slits in top of crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° then 40 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(preacher cookies)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook over medium heat; boil for 2 minutes, stirring all the time, and remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: hope's white chili
directions: Put beans in medium pan and cover with water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and allow to simmer 20 minutes. Drain and discard water. Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces and brown, if desired. Put all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir to mix thoroughly. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours.

title: duie butter cake
directions: Mix the softened butter, cake mix and 1 egg together (should be like cookie dough), then spread the cookie dough on an 11 x 13-inch cookie pan.
This should be spread evenly on the cookie sheet.
Then take the remaining ingredients and mix them together. (Use a mixer if desired.)
Pour over the cookie dough and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When finished, take 1/4 cup of powdered sugar and sprinkle all over top of cake.
When cool, cut into 2 x 2-inch squares and enjoy!

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; 325° for glass pan.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle graham crumbs over butter. Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly browned. Cool thoroughly at room temperature before cutting. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: cashew chicken with broccoli
directions: Lightly brown nuts in oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat, about 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Saute onion and garlic in skillet 2 minutes.
Add chicken.
Saute until golden brown, about 8 minutes.
Add broccoli, 3/4 cup broth and soy.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining 1/4 cup broth.
Stir into skillet.
Simmer, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Boil 1 minute.
Return cashews to skillet with salt and pepper.

title: banana salad
directions: Combine boiling water and Jell-O.
When dissolved, add cold water.
When Jell-O begins to thicken, add drained pineapple and bananas.
Chill until set.

title: fish soup with stuffed pasta
directions: Brown onion, celery and garlic in oil.
Add next 5 ingredients. Cook covered 1/2 hour.
(This part can be made ahead and refrigerated.)
Bring to a boil.
Add fish and cook 5 minutes. Cook ravioli.
Add to soup with shrimp, wine and parsley.
Serve hot.

title: russian macaroni
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Cook covered for 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve topped with chopped tomatoes and basil.

title: hungarian sauerkraut
directions: Remove bacon.
Into grease, put onions and saute until transparent.
Cook noodles not quite tender; drain.
Add mushrooms; drain.
Cook cabbage and sauerkraut in a little water. Mix all ingredients together carefully.
Bake 1 hour in uncovered casserole dish at 300° for 25 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and butter in a large mixing bowl; beat well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Gradually add flour mixture to cheese mixture, mixing until dough is no longer crumbly.
Shape mixture into a ball.

title: irish cream
directions: Combine and blend for 3 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps for 2 weeks.

title: ham pate
directions: Combine 1 package of cream cheese, ham, onion and pecans, mixing well.
Line a 2-cup mold or bowl with plastic wrap.
Spoon mixture into mold, pressing firmly.
Cover and chill 3 hours. Unmold onto a serving plate.
Beat remaining package of cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Spread over ham mixture.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: potato salad
directions: Cream potatoes.
Dice eggs.
Add Miracle Whip, mustard and diced pickles to taste.
Drain pimentos and add diced onion.
Mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese; add flavoring and sugar and cream together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in flour.
Grease and flour tube pan and pour mixture in and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. (Usually takes 1 hour and 45 minutes.)

title: cherry and applesauce salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water until dissolved.
Add applesauce and lemon juice.
Then pour into an oiled salad mold and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook until brown.
Pour over popped corn and mix.
If not crisp, bake in slow oven at 250°.
Extra delicious!

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk and then vanilla.
Pour into Pyrex; sprinkle with nutmeg and place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until mixture does not adhere to knife.

title: ham 'n' swiss loaf(in honor of fern hedgewood)
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour; mix remaining 3 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat water, mustard and margarine to 125° to 130°; stir into flour mixture.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
Knead 4 minutes.
On greased baking sheet, roll dough to 14 x 12-inches.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and pickle down center third of dough length.
Make cuts from filling to dough edges at 1-inch intervals along sides of filling.
Bring strips from opposite sides of filling together; twist and place ends at an angle across filling; cover.

title: robert redford dessert
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix butter, flour and nuts until crumbled.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick quiche
directions: Beat eggs, milk, Bisquick, salt and pepper together.
Pour the mixture over meat, vegetables and cheese in buttered pie plate. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Test with knife in the middle.
The Bisquick will rise to the top to form a crust.

title: alice's rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, salt, margarine and water to boil in a small saucepan.
Let cook until rice is tender.
Drain.
Do not rinse. Add sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla and raisins.
Mix well.
Let set. Bring milk and Jell-O mix to a boil over medium heat.
Stir into the rice mix.
Bake in oven until the top shakes like custard. Remove from oven.
Let cool for about 15 minutes, then cover with a clear wrap, i.e., Glad Wrap or Saran Wrap, for about 30 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes about 6 (4 ounce) servings.

title: party potato bake
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet. Saut onion and pepper in fat. Add cheese, milk, salt and pepper until melted. Add potatoes; mix lightly. Pour into 10 x 6 dish. Top with bacon. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until tender.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Heat water, margarine and bouillon together for 1 minute on High.
Stir in potatoes.
Cook, covered, for 6 minutes on full power.
Stir.
Cook an additional 4 minutes on High and stir again.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
These potatoes cook better if pieces are smaller.

title: cucumbers with sour cream
directions: Peel the cucumber and slice thinly.
Place in a bowl and set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour the mixture over the cucumbers and toss lightly to mix.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together; then add milk.
Add all four ingredients to the butter in the skillet.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over biscuits or plain yellow cake.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix flour with the other ingredients to the consistency of a pie crust.
Roll out.
Cut about 1/2 inch in thickness.
Bake in a quick oven.

title: chicken quiche
directions: You will need a greased pie tin.

title: chicken almondine casserole
directions: Mix all together and toss lightly.
Place in greased casserole.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat well.
Add pineapple, then flour.
Mix fruit in a little flour so it won't settle to the bottom.
Put aluminum foil in pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fettuccine with peas and ham
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in large saucepan.
Add shallots and saute until soft.
Add mushrooms; increase heat to high and cook until mushrooms are lightly browned.
Remove vegetables and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine to same pan.
Melt and add flour; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add milk slowly, stirring with wire whisk.
Add salt and cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add peas and cook 30 seconds longer.
Blend together sauce, vegetables, ham, fettuccine and 3/4 of cheese.
Season with pepper and remainder of cheese.
Serves 8.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Simmer cream of chicken soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and sour cream.
Add diced chicken to mixture.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips over low heat.
Pour over cereal in a large bowl.
Dump sugar on top.
Dump cereal into a clean unused grocery bag and shake slowly.
Pour out on wax paper to cool.

title: cream cheese pancakes
directions: Combine self-rising flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Cook pancakes until tops are covered with bubbles and edges appear cooked.
Turn and cook other side.
Serve pancakes with warm maple syrup and, if desired, bacon.
Yield:
12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: beef and cabbage dinner
directions: Melt oleo in large skillet.
Add cabbage and onion, mixing well.
Arrange potatoes over cabbage; sprinkle with caraway seed. Crumble beef over potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all and cover skillet.
Cook over low heat until meat and potatoes are done, about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Let stand overnight; drain. Add rest of the ingredients.
Boil all together for 3 minutes. Seal in hot clean jars.

title: karen's chess pie
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine on low-medium heat. Pour in sugar, stirring until dissolved well. Add vinegar and vanilla extract. Stir together and bring to a rolling bubble on simmer heat. Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool slightly. Beat eggs and cornmeal together in a small bowl. Add egg-cornmeal mixture to the cooled saucepan mixture and squeezed lemon. Blend well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion, mushrooms and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Combine egg and Ricotta cheese.
Layer uncooked noodles, sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella, ending with sauce.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup water over all.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix
together and chill.
When chilled, shape and cover with 3 tablespoons parsley flakes or 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: angel pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Mix crackers and 1 cup pecans and fold into egg whites.
Spoon into 9-inch grease pan to form shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream, 2 tablespoons sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Whip until thick and fill shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Measure dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add soup and shortening.
Beat at low to medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes more, scraping bowl often.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool, right side up, in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool, if desired; sprinkle with confectioners sugar or use cream cheese frosting.

title: the babitt's amaretto whipped cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease bottom of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Combine graham crackers, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press on bottom of spring-form pan.
Evenly distribute coconut on baking sheet.
Toast coconut until golden brown (about 15 minutes).
Set aside.

title: potato rolls
directions: Add egg with oil, sugar and salt.
At room temperature, take 1 cup milk and potatoes that are lukewarm.
Thin with the remaining milk from the quart.
Add dissolved yeast.
Lastly, add flour until you have a soft dough.
Let rise once in oiled crock until double in size.
Punch down; make into rolls or bread.
It can be refrigerated up to 3 days.
Shape into desired bread.
Let rise again to double.
Bake at 375°.
Bake rolls for 20 to 25 minutes, bread for 30 minutes and monkey bread for 40 minutes.

title: aunt elsie's cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
To make cocoa, mix 1/3 cup of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour in crust.
Chill an hour or two before adding the top.

title: play dough fudge
directions: Mix together all ingredients with a wooden spoon.
If mixture seems too sticky, add more powdered milk.
Give each child a 2-inch ball to mold as play dough.
Feel free to decorate creations with garnishes such as raisins, nuts, Cheerios, etc. Keeps up to 1 week in Ziploc in the fridge.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Blend together rice, salt, soups, milk, celery and onion.
Pour in oblong pan.
Salt and pepper chicken and place on top of rice mixture.
Bake uncovered for 2 1/2 hours.
Put in 350° oven.
After cooked through good, turn heat down to 300° and cook until rice is tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk to a soft ball stage (236 degrees).
Add marshmallow, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix together well.
Pour into a buttered 9x13 pan.

title: ninth street house tea(from ninth street house restaurant in paducah, kentucky)
directions: *I use frozen Minute Maid.

title: pork with raisin-onion sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rub all sides of pork with garlic and sprinkle with pepper.
Roast until pork is cooked (approximately 20 minutes).
While meat is cooking, prepare sauce.

title: warm mexican nacho dip
directions: Use mini crock-pot, electric skillet or casserole dish on a warming plate to keep dip hot and cheese melted.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Combine eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Add onions, potatoes and butter.
Bake in a 9-inch square baking dish (top with paprika) for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and top is brown and crisp.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: to cook prime rib
directions: Have the rib roast at room temperature.
Salt, garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Stand roast up on bone side and cover loosely with tinfoil.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 1 hour (depending on how done you want it cooked).
Turn oven off.
Leave oven door closed for at least 4 hours without being opened!
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.
(This time is also according to how done you like your steak.)

title: lenas pasta rustica
directions: In large Dutch oven over medium heat, warm oil.
Add onion; stir until golden, about 5 minutes. Add garlic, stir for 1 minute. Add sausage breaking it into bite-size pieces and cook until no longer pink about 6 minutes.
Stir in spices and add tomatoes with puree and bring to a boil.	Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer, stirring occasionally until thickened, 10-12 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings.	Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a baking dish.
In large pot 3/4 full of water, add pasta and salt; boil until barely al dente, 10-12 minutes.
Drain well.	In a large bowl, toss pasta with sauce, ricotta and fontina.
Spread in prepared baking dish and sprinkle with Parmigiano-Reggiano.
Bake until cheeses are melted and tips of pasta are crusty, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve hot.
Serves six to eight.

title: potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes, let cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate and serve on the leaf of lettuce.

title: ann snyder's brownies
directions: Combine the eggs, oil and sugar; beat well.
Add cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 3 cups of hot water.
Put in shallow pan in refrigerator to set.
When gelatin is set, melt marshmallows in milk in top of double boiler.
Cool.
Dice gelatin and put in a large bowl with fruit cocktail and nuts.
Add whipped topping and marshmallow mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Place in refrigerator and cool for several hours before serving.

title: asparagus puffs
directions: Open crescent rolls and separate.
Spread cheese on each triangle.
Place 2 asparagus stalks on each triangle.
Roll up. Follow crescent roll directions on package.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (until golden).
Paint with egg whites for a glaze before baking, if desired.

title: aunt sara's cookies
directions: Put eggs in bowl and mix slightly.
Melt Crisco (if used) and beat a little, then add flavoring and beat more with sugar.
Last add flour and baking powder.
(Add only as much flour as it takes so dough is not too sticky.)
Roll dough and use a cookie cutter or you can roll dough into a rope and shape or make "S" shape cookies.
Bake in oven on 350° until a nice golden brown.
If you want, you can mix dough with your hands.

title: ground beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt cheese in with ground beef, stirring constantly.
Pour into bowl with salsa mix.
Serve with white tostada corn chips.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Make peanut butter and Ritz crackers.
Melt white chocolate in top of double boiler.
Dip peanut crackers into white chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: fran's baked beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Mix in catsup, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange bacon strips across the top of beans.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: hearty ham chowder
directions: In heavy saucepan, saute onion in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate jumbles
directions: Mix together as given.
Roll out thin.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Beat 1 egg and brush top.
Sprinkle with sugar (regular). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter and add mushrooms and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes. Combine all other ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal fettucini sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Add seafood or chicken.
Pour over cooked fettucini.

title: meatballs
directions: Pour tomato juice over bread crumbs.
Add meat, pepper, salt, garlic, meat loaf seasoning, onion and chopped pepper.
Mix well and shape into round balls.
Place in a casserole dish.
Combine the catsup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Stir well.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes and add melted shortening.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk to yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured surface and knead until dough can be handled.
Shape into a ball. Place in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Shape into rolls as desired.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Dough will keep 1 week.)

title: curried pork chops
directions: Brown chops on skillet, then arrange in single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion in oil.
Add flour, sugar, curry powder and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
In a bowl, stir consomme, ketchup and water together and place over chops.
Add apples; bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cajun burgers
directions: Dried red pepper flakes or any other hot pepper may be added. Mix all together and form burgers.
Great for the grill.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake chocolate cake as per box directions.
When cool, break up cake into pieces and place in 2 foil lasagna cake pans.
Cover with crumbled Heath bars.
Pour pudding over candy.
Top with Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: quick cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing together. Form into a ball. Take ball and roll on top of crushed walnuts. Serve with crackers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail and mix well with cream cheese.
Then mix fruit cocktail and remaining ingredients with this and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine in a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake in 375° oven until knife comes out clean.
The last 20 minutes, cover casserole with fried onion bits.

title: green jello salad
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Fold in jello.
Add cottage cheese, coconut, pineapple and walnuts. Chill.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Sift first five ingredients into mixing bowl.
Stir shortening, eggs, milk and apples for 15 seconds.
Pour this over dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full. Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
(When sides begin to leave pan.)
Serve hot or cool.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In 8-quart Dutch oven, heat oil and brown beef.
Remove meat. Add carrots, celery, onions and mushrooms in drippings, until lightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Return beef to pan and add water and the next 6 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring. Reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours until barley and meat are tender.
Add broccoli and string beans and simmer for 15 minutes.
Yields 16 cups.
Contains 185 calories per serving.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Layer the ingredients in order in a spring-form pan.
Refrigerate overnight and serve with Tostitos.

title: savory shepherd's pie
directions: In skillet,
brown
beef
and
cook onion until tender. Drain off fat.
Stir
in
soup,
salt
and thyme.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole
dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edge of casserole. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Heat milk.
Let cool slightly before you add yeast.
Mix all ingredients.
Let raise until double in size.
Knead, roll out and cut into rolls.
Let raise again.
Spread mixture with oil and cinnamon.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes.
Scoop pulp out of potatoes and place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients (milk until smooth consistency). Top with marshmallows or pecans and bake at 350° until marshmallows are light brown.

title: chocolate chunk banana bread
directions: Stir eggs, bananas, oil and milk until well blended.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir until just moistened. Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pan to 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool on a wire rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Mix dry ingredients and combine the two.
Add vanilla and walnuts; mix by hand.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hard candy or rock candy
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart saucepan.

Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils. Continue boiling without stirring until small amount is very brittle when dropped into water or 310° or hard crack on candy thermometer.
Cook slowly at end so syrup will not discolor. Remove from heat.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Stir only to mix. Pour on cookie pans, lightly greased.
Let mixture cool to hard. Break up candy.
Keep cool in summer.

title: breakfast hash brown pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix hash brown potatoes and oil in bowl.
Press into a 10-inch pie plate, forming crust.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add layers of cheese, sausage, onion and eggs, beaten with evaporated milk.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: one of each soup(yield: 4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Simmer vegetables and fruits in broth in a 3-quart heavy saucepan, covered, until very tender, about 12 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° to 400°, about an hour.

title: confederate coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup of butter and 1 cup of sugar.
Add milk and unbeaten eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Blend into the creamed mixture, adding a dash of nutmeg. Pour batter into a well-greased loaf cake pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, cinnamon, nuts and sugar.
Dot well with butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chesapeake bay crab soup
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart pot and saute onion and green pepper until onion is soft.
Add fish stock and rice.
Simmer, partially covered, 15 minutes.
Add crabmeat, tomato, chili powder, paprika and Worcestershire and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and nutmeg; set aside in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 3-inch pan.
Mix apples, lemon juice and butter.
Mix in dry mixture.
Add water and crust.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cooked chicken, celery, onion, cooked rice, Hellmann's mayonnaise and cream of chicken soup.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until mixture bubbles up.
Remove from oven; sprinkle cornflakes over top, then almonds. Bake for another 15 minutes or until it begins to brown.
This serves 18 people.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onions and margarine. Cook squash or use canned squash. Mix all ingredients with cornbread and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ski pot stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a large ovenproof casserole with a tight fitting cover.
Put in preheated oven (275°) and let it do its thing for 5 hours or more.

title: stombolee
directions: Thaw dough and press into 11 x 14-inch pan.
Cover with a damp cloth for 5 minutes; press again.
Beat egg and brush half on dough.
Layer the meats and Provolone until gone.
Add Parmesan to remainder of egg and pour over meat.
Spread other half of dough and place on top.
Seal edges and brush top with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti or pizza sauce.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: First brown ground beef, sausage and onion and drain off excess grease.
Add soups and Ro-Tel with 2 pounds Velveeta cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve hot over Doritos.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well before using.
Can be used to marinate coleslaw, cucumbers or just as a salad dressing.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In heavy skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add 6 green onions, onion, green peppers, garlic and celery; saute until vegetables are thoroughly wilted, about 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and wine.
Cook, stirring often, until liquid is reduced by 1/2.

title: cole slaw
directions: Add ingredients to grated cabbage.

title: popcorn balls(very easy)
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, bring to a boil over low heat the Karo, margarine, water, powdered sugar and marshmallows.
Pour over popcorn; toss to coat evenly.
Form into balls (use cold water on your hands while shaping the balls).

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft. Add beef broth and water. Simmer 1 hour.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the ???.
Dredge the blueberries 1 cup of the flour.
Sift 1 cup flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Gently fold the dredged blueberries in the batter.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes, then remove.

title: cauliflower in cheese sauce
directions: Cook cauliflower as directed on package and place in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine.
Add flour and mustard.
Stir until well mixed.
Gradually add milk.
When slightly thickened, add 1/2 cup cheese.
When cheese has melted, pour over the cauliflower and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Cook with marshmallows until melted.
Add Jell-O and let almost set. Add nuts, pineapple, whipped topping and cottage cheese. Refrigerate until the next day and ready to serve.

title: francis marion reception punch
directions: Combine orange juice, ice water, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Mix thoroughly and chill.
To serve, pour half the mixture into a large punch bowl and add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Use the rest of the mixture and ginger ale as needed to keep the punch alive.
The punch may be sweetened with sugar dissolved in water, if desired.
Serves 100.

title: pizza crusts
directions: In small bowl, combine water and yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Combine flour and salt; stir in yeast until moistened.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add flour to prevent sticking.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease all sides.
Let rise in draft-free place about 2 hours. Punch dough down.
Cover with inverted bowl; let rest 15 minutes. Makes 2 crusts.
Cover with your favorite sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until quite thick; add liquid and extract, then flour, salt and baking powder, sifted together. Fold in gently; turn into large shallow pan lined with oiled paper.
Spread smooth.
Bake in quick oven at 375° for about 12 minutes.
Turn upside-down on cloth or heavy paper, sprinkled with sugar.
Tear off oiled paper and spread with jam or jelly. Roll up quickly and trim ends.

title: ham and swiss casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, green pepper and onion. Stir in noodles, ham and cheese. Spoon into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: razorback cookies
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, combine margarine and milk. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Add sugar, cocoa and salt. Microwave on High 3 minutes, stirring several times.
Add vanilla extract and peanut butter; stir until blended.
Stir in coconut, oats and nuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased waxed paper.
Cool at room temperature until firm.
Store in airtight container.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk; add vanilla.
Pour over butter. Pour the peaches over this batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tomato salad
directions: Slice tomatoes into eighths.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the tomatoes.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients together well.
Cook over medium-high heat.
Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat to boiling all ingredients except popped corn.
Stir constantly.
Put popped corn in 2 pans and pour 1/2 caramel mixture over each.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mock chicken fried steak
directions: Combine egg, 3/4 cup cracker crumbs, milk, onion, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce. Add ground round. Mix well. Shape into patties and coat with remaining cracker crumbs. Cook in margarine about 4 minutes on each side or until done the way you like.

title: baked salmon turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and flake salmon.
(Removing the bones is optional.)

title: baked noodles and apples
directions: Cook noodles, drain and rinse in hot water; drain again.
Add butter and cheese, stirring until melted.
Combine apples and brown sugar; add to noodles.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, covered.
Remove from oven, uncover, stir well and return to oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, pepper, onions and peas in order.
Spread mayonnaise on top like frosting.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise. Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise and sugar.
Put crumbled bacon on top.
Do not stir.
Best made the night before serving.
Toss just before serving.

title: cucumber rounds
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Cut into rounds with biscuit cutter. Spread with cream cheese and mayonnaise mixed with dressing. Mix.
Sprinkle dill seed on each round.

title: real old fashioned lemonade
directions: In a large pitcher, combine lemon juice and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Makes 6 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Chop in casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream and water together and pour over chicken.
Top with crackers that are crumbled, poppy seed and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Chop onion and brown in bacon grease.
Add peeled and diced potatoes.
Peel and slice carrots and add.
Cover in large pot with water and let boil with bay leaf, about 30 minutes.
Add meat and instant potatoes until broth thickens.
Bring to boil; add marjoram and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Salt to taste.
This soup tastes good with rye bread or corn bread.

title: no bake fudge nougats
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Blend in chocolate chips, flour, cracker crumbs, nuts and vanilla. Beat until thick.
Spread in well-greased 9-inch square pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and cooking oil.
Mix well. This will be thick.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Place bacon in a large, heavy pot and cook until crisp.
Add scallions and cook an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Add crab meat, salt, wine or juice and chicken stock and bring to a boil. Combine cream with potato or cornstarch and add to soup.
Stir until thickened and serve. Yields 6 servings.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Crumble hash browns; mix with onions, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake in glass baking dish until brown at 350°.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of a glass 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread refried beans next. Brown hamburger meat, adding garlic salt and picante sauce to taste.
Layer this mixture on next. Top with cheese, sliced tomatoes, grated lettuce and chopped onions. Serve hot or cold.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions; add salt to taste.
Pour boiling water over this and let stand 20 minutes.
Drain and add vinegar and other dry ingredients.
Cook, not over 20 minutes.
May add green tomatoes and grind them with the peppers.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: avocado jello
directions: Combine and
mix
jello, hot water and unflavored gelatin; set aside.
Combine
and mix in a blender mashed avocado, milk, sugar, cold water and mayonnaise.	Combine both mixtures in a bowl; stir.
Pour
into
a
greased jello mold or a container of your choice.
Place in refrigerator until hardened.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in an 11 x 13-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put cooked broccoli into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli and cover with crackers.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan; heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.
Cool mixture to 105° to 115°. Combine yeast and warm water in a 1 cup liquid measuring cup, let stand five minutes.
Combine yeast mixture, milk mixture, egg substitute, 1 cup flour and oats in a large mixing bowl, mixing well.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes).
Place dough in a large bowl coated with cooking spray, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down; cover and let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough in half and roll each in a 12-inch square.
Spread each square with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Combine 3/4 cup brown sugar, raisins and cinnamon; sprinkle over each square.

title: cornmeal play dough(not for human consumption)
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead with your hands.
If the dough is too stiff, add water and continue to knead.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine eggs and sugar. Add pumpkin.
Mix flour and spices together then add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into greased and lined (with wax paper) 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool 15 minutes then roll cake in towel while you mix the filling.

title: stuffed pita pockets(serves at least 4)
directions: Cook spinach in microwave according to package directions; cool, drain and squeeze out liquid and set aside.
Scramble egg and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in the butter (do not let them soften); remove from skillet and set aside.
Saute onion in the oil and remove from skillet.
Brown meat in skillet, breaking beef up, then add the garlic and saute for 30 seconds.

Then add cooked onion, the herbs, pepper, bouillon cube and water; cover and simmer on low heat for 5 minutes or until bouillon is dissolved. Uncover and add spinach, mushrooms and scrambled egg and heat through.
Taste and adjust seasonings with salt and pepper if desired.

title: minted snowballs
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in small saucepan.
Place on medium heat and stir until all is dissolved.
Boil 2 minutes; remove from heat and add peppermint extract; with toothpick, dip each marshmallow in hot syrup and then roll in coconut.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown hamburger and add remaining ingredients (except for cheese).
Can be cooked on stove or crockpot.
When hot, serve with grated cheese on top.
Chili will be thick.

title: beef burgundy(serves 10)
directions: Dredge meat with flour in paper bag; saute meat, onion and garlic until brown.
Add mushrooms, liquid and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours, stirring frequently, until meat is tender.
Add more water or wine if necessary.
Serve with macaroni casserole.

title: chinese noodle salad with five-spice chicken
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart pan, bring 3 quarts water to boiling on high heat.
Add noodles and cook, uncovered, just until tender to bite, 2 or 3 minutes.
Drain; immerse in cold water until cool.
Drain again and put in a large bowl.
Add 1/3 cup dressing, cilantro, ginger and lemon peel; mix gently and set aside.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix and then freeze.

title: ryan's brownies
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, melt 6 ounces chocolate chips and margarine.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Add chocolate chips and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add water to make 1 gallon of punch.
Dilute with 1 quart of ginger ale to 1 gallon of punch.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease and flour 10-inch pie pan.
Blend all ingredients together in blender until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into 11 x 15-inch pan. Spread melted chocolate morsels on top.
Chill until set and cut into bars.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together Crisco and flour until coarse crumbs.
Mix egg, water and vinegar together, then mix into flour mixture. Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Divide in half.
Makes two 9-inch double crust pies or three 8-inch double crust pies.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate or an 8-inch quiche dish.
Set aside.
In a covered medium saucepan, cook fresh corn in a small amount of boiling, lightly salted water for 4 minutes.
(Or cook frozen corn according to package directions.) Drain well.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix egg and milk; stir into dry mixture.
Add melted shortening and mix thoroughly.
Pour into hot skillet with 1 tablespoon shortening.
Bake in a preheated oven at 450° until golden brown.

title: rhubarb coffee cake(freezes well)
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add flour and salt. Mix soda with buttermilk and add flour alternately with buttermilk-soda mixture to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and blend again.
Fold in rhubarb.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle topping over top and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Cook or bake the chicken until tender.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook and stir for 5 minutes or until golden.

title: chicken bites
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix until well blended.
Stir in chicken, celery and pimento; set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles; press perforations to seal.
Spread about 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture over each dough rectangle, leaving 1/2 inch margin on one long side and no margin on other sides.
Roll dough, jelly roll fashion, starting at long side with filling spread to edge; pinch seams to seal.
Cut each roll into 5 pieces; place seam side down on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: diet chili
directions: Cook in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine soy and vinegar in a tightly covered container.
Add cucumbers, salt and pepper.
Marinate for 4 hours and invert container overnight.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in a medium skillet until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place triangles with elongated points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust; seal perforations. Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with hash brown potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake 5 more minutes.
Garnish with pimento and fresh oregano, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shake and bake for chicken or fish
