directions: Combine all ingredients and store in the refrigerator.
Makes enough to coat 2 to 3 pounds of chicken or fish.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 round cake pans (8 or 9-inch) and line bottoms with wax paper.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat until blended thoroughly.
Pour into pans.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: good potatoes
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese over potato mixture.
Mix together 2 cups cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over potato and cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
You can add more potatoes if needed and bake up to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Form into balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs. Dust nuts and lemon peel in a little flour. Alternately add dry ingredients with milk. Add nuts and peel. Divide into 2 small greased and floured pans. Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until done.

title: cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until blended.
Mix the flour with the baking powder.
Add to the butter mixture with the cream and lemon extract.
Mix until a stiff dough forms.
Chill for 30 minutes if necessary.
Using 1 teaspoonful of dough at a time, roll into small balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheets. Press a halved cherry into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly golden and set.
Cool and store in an airtight container or freeze for longer use.

title: microwave orange carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: instant boiled custard
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Let sit in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream oil, margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Make small balls and mash with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: country ham & corn casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 12 x 8 inch baking dish. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown and set.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 1-2 minutes to melt cheese. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Cut into squares, makes 6 servings.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a bowl; stir well. Gradually add water and next 2 ingredients, stirring with a wire whisk until blended; set aside.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Barely melt butter.
Add flour and nuts.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely. Mix cream cheese with sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on cake when cooled.
Mix pudding with milk and extract.
Blend until thick. Pour over second layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: zesty vegetable salad
directions: Clean and cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Steam vegetables until lightly tender.
Remove from the heat and pour the Viva Italian dressing over the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 to 5 hours.
Shake or toss the salad in a covered bowl, then serve.

title: chorizo-beer chili
directions: Brown sausage and beef in a large stew pot. Drain and add onions and garlic.
Return and add other ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve with cheese.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Add chopped pimento for color.
You can also add a can of bean sprouts (washed and drained) and cooked carrots (sliced thin or diced).
Mix vegetables together.
Mix the oil, sugar, vinegar and salt together and pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly and let stand in refrigerator overnight before using.
This will keep for days and still be delicious.

title: vegetable appetizer
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing. Spread mix on dough after cooling.
Garnish with vegetables, chopped (broccoli, carrots, radishes, celery, etc.) and grated cheese.
Chill, cut in desired squares and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; reserve 3 tablespoons drippings in pan. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onions in drippings until tender.
Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish. Bake 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: carol's crumb cake
directions: Make up package of yellow cake mix as directed. Pour into buttered and floured pan (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine all other ingredients.
Place crumbs on cake and return to oven 10 more minutes.

title: southern cavier
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill 24 hours.
Remove garlic.
Chill for 2 days to 2 weeks before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Just mix all the ingredients and bake.
Your family won't believe those cookies are a meal in themselves.
Excellent for taking camping or for the late to work/school group.

title: clam balls
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Mix filling cubes, eggs, clams, red pepper, salt and pepper, celery seed, Old Bay and parsley.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover last 15 minutes.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix ingredients until blended, using only as much juice as needed to make a good dip consistency.
Chill well before serving.

title: onion sauce hamburger steaks
directions: Mix hamburger with green onions; mix well and shape into patties.
Fry in medium saucepan until almost done.
Pour tomato sauce over meat and finish cooking 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over tomatoes.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix; put in greased baking dish.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder. soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to first mixture and mix thoroughly.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cod fish cakes
directions: Soak codfish
overnight.
Chip codfish into a bowl.
Add onion, dash of pepper, lots of thyme and one stalk of scallion. Add flour and
water, enough to obtain a cake batter consistency. Let everything
sit
a few minutes.
Heat frying pan.
Add enough oil to
cover
entire
pan.
Add droplets of batter into pan.
Put as much in pan as pan can hold.
Flip once and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix mixture well and set aside at room temperature for 1 hour. Then cook in deep fryer.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: red chili sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: hearty beef pot pie  with cornmeal cheese crust
directions: Brown beef in hot oil; remove.
Cook green pepper and onion in drippings until tender.
Add beef, corn, undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, peppers, chili powder, sugar, 2/3 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and pie filling.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cake cool.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk in a bowl.
Melt oleo in the baking dish, then pour in batter.
Put fruit on top.
Crust will rise to top as it cooks. Bake until brown.

title: carol's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; do not overcook.
Drain potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except eggs, pickles, celery and onion.
Fold until almost smooth, then fold in diced eggs and pickles.
If desired, add celery and onion.
Chill overnight.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: In saucepan, mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt; stir well, then add milk, egg yolks, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and cook on stove until it becomes thick (usually it boils).
Place in 10-inch pie shell when cool.
Beat 2 egg whites with 6 teaspoons sugar; place on top of pie and brown in hot oven for a few minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and let cool.
Add remaining items except parsley and stir gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Yields 12 servings.

title: kuchen
directions: Prepare dough, adding sugar and extra shortening to make more crumbly.
Roll very thin and line pie tins.
(Don't add milk until ready to roll.)
You may use any fresh fruit: plums, raspberries, cherries, peaches.

title: old fashion brownie cookies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa.
Cool and add sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for about 8-10 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Crumble bag of Doritos and place in bottom of large baking dish.
Brown hamburger; drain and add onion and garlic powder. Cover; reduce heat.
In a saucepan, heat soups, picante sauce and green chilies.
Pour a layer of hamburger mixture over chips; sprinkle 1/2 of cheese on hamburger.
Then pour soup mixture and add rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Add milk, pudding and melted margarine.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Take from heat and add sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 6-inch greased pan.

title: peanut butter clubhouse sandwich
directions: Spread 2 crisp breads with 1 tablespoon peanut butter a piece. Sprinkle carrots over peanut butter on 1 crisp bread.
Place second crisp bread, peanut butter side up, over carrots.
Place banana slices on the peanut butter, then drizzle with honey.
Top with the third crisp bread.
Using a serrated knife, cut sandwich in half lengthwise.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and cool completely.
Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, then mix in cooled jello.
Mix all ingredients into whipped Milnot, then pour in 13 x 9-inch dish. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: christmas red and green salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Add juice from small can of pineapple and enough water to make 1 cup liquid. Cool.
Add marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
Add celery, cheese, nuts, mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Add a few drops of green coloring.
Let congeal, but not through.

title: german steaks
directions: Take steaks and spread 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard across. Spread onion and parsnips across each steak. Put 3 pickle sticks and carrot sticks in center and roll up. Insert toothpicks to hold together. Put in center of roaster pan. Make a nest of potatoes and rest of pickles and carrots around steaks. Sprinkle with leftover onion and parsnips. Cover with mushroom soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in a 2-quart glass measuring cup.
Place in microwave and cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir well. Add peanuts and cook for another 3 1/2 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending together.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup will be very hot.
Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto aluminum foil and spread as thin as possible.
Let cool and break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots, flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt.
stir in eggs, oil, and vanilla extract, mixing well.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top of cake while still warm.
Yield:
one 3-layer cake.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients together and stir over medium heat until mixture lumps together in center of pan or mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat; cool and knead while still warm.
Store in airtight container.
Add food coloring, unsweetened Kool-Aid for small glitter or spices.
Also for fresh smell.

title: yeast breads
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups water, sugar and salt.
Crumble yeast into mixture; stir until dissolved.
Add 2 eggs and shortening. Mix first with spoon, then by hand the potatoes and flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator for about 2 hours.
Remove; shape dough into desired rolls, coffee cake, etc.
Cover; let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until light.
Bake according to directions for each type roll or pastry.
Bake rolls at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: beef goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Drain.
Sprinkle uncooked noodles over meat.
Combine water, tomato sauce and soup mix.
Pour over noodles in skillet.
Do not stir.
Cover and bring to boil. Simmer for about 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: red rice
directions: Saut onions and peppers in bacon grease. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish. Cover tightly and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in plenty of water.
Cook for 1 hour, adding more water if necessary until tender.
Remove from stove and add balance of ingredients.
Mix; pour into baking pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: boiled ham biscuits
directions: Slice
precooked
dinner
rolls down middle lengthwise. Lay flat on foil or cookie sheet.
Mix mustard, margarine and Worcestershire sauce and spread thin layer on biscuits.
Next, lay ham on bottom of bread.
Add a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Top with top of bread.
Bake in oven a few minutes just before serving.
Bake just until cheese is slightly melted.

title: jean's turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and liquids.
Toss lightly as you slowly drizzle butter and liquids over crumbs and seasonings.

title: tea for 50
directions: Make syrup of water and sugar; cool and add juices and tea. Just before serving, add cold ginger ale.
Serve over ice in tall glasses.
Garnish with fresh mint.

title: hershey's classic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl,
beat butter, sugar brown, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until creamy.
Add eggs; beat well. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by round teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: mincemeat refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, lemon peel and egg. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with mincemeat.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Shape in rolls.
Chill 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° about 15 minutes.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Let boil about 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Pour into greased pan and press down until cookies are firm.
Cut when cool.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs and milk.
Add flour and baking powder.
Knead and roll thin and cut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream gravy
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and sprinkle with lots of paprika. Top with butter patties.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cashew
directions: Cut chicken into bite size
pieces
and
place
in
a 2 quart round casserole.
Combine
wine,
soy sauce, cornstarch, garlic and ginger in a
1 cup glass measure.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring midway through
cooking.
Add
peppers,
re-cover and microwave on High for 3
to 4 minutes, stirring midway through cooking. Sprinkle with cashews and let stand for 3 minutes.

title: sandy's skip and go naked(a very unique drink)
directions: Pour over blender of ice and crush.
Mix and pour over the rocks.

title: quiche muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place cottage cheese in a food processor and process until smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl. Process egg whites until foamy.
Add next 5 ingredients and process until smooth.
Add egg mixture to cottage cheese.
Stir in cheese, onions and bacon. Fill greased large muffin tins 2/3 full and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Makes 10 muffins.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix with pineapple.
Pour mixture into well buttered baking dish. Crush crackers and mix with margarine.
Spread on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Mix all ingredients by hand until well mixed.
Then on high speed for 5 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: toasty onion sticks
directions: Cut
ends
off	bread.	Spread	with Onion Butter.
Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.	Makes about 5 dozen sticks.

title: white seafoam candy
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until spins a thread from a spoon and thread blows out.
Don't undercook!
Remove from heat.
Pour slowly into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat until it becomes stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool and cut into pieces.

title: wassail(hot punch)
directions: Heat the first 2 ingredients to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes longer. Serve hot.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers until fine. The mix with other ingredients well.
Pack mixture in vanilla wafer box and freeze. Keep all leftover cake refrigerated after cutting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix lightly. Add flour mixture and blend. Grease pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 small loaves.

title: cherry stuff
directions: Whip until stiff the egg whites and cream of tartar.
Mix in rest of ingredients except cherry filling and Cool Whip.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: vegetable and cheese stuffed shells
directions: Cook vegetables in oil until tender.
Stir in flour and milk; cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cottage cheese, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Stuff shells, put in shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions. Mix all ingredients, except Ritz crackers, in casserole dish.
Spread crushed Ritz crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: persimmon cake
directions: Mix nuts, raisins, sugar, fruits, persimmon pulp and oil in a large size bowl.
Sift flour, spices, soda and salt together.
Mix beaten eggs and milk.
Combine nut mixture with egg mixture; stir in dry ingredients until well blended.
Oil tube or angel food pan well; spoon cake mixture into prepared pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until a toothpick comes out clean in the center.
Makes a 5 to 6-pound cake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Parboil or steam cabbage.
Mix soups, margarine and milk. Heat slowly and stir.
Put cabbage in casserole dish, pour mixture over.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Cut one roll of cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices and arrange on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs with electric mixer until well blended. Spread on cookie dough slices.
Slice second roll into 1/4-inch slices and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, dissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk and butter until warm (105° to 115°). Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup flour; beat 2 minutes at high speed.
With spoon, stir in enough remaining flour to make a very stiff batter.
Grease top of dough.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate batter for 2 hours or up to 2 days.

title: italian green beans
directions: Melt butter.
Add all seasonings, plus onions and garlic.
Let cook 5 minutes, then add beans and carrots.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Spread chopped pecans, and few marshmallows on top.
Chill and serve.
Looks pretty in a glass bowl.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs.
Make paste with cocoa and vinegar.
Add to butter mixture.
Beat until fluffy. Sift the flour, salt and soda together.
Add coloring to milk. Add, alternating with flour, to butter mixture.
Pour in three 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, cool on rack before removing.

title: ruth's shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni and shrimp; drain and cool.

In a large bowl, mix macaroni, shrimp, eggs, onions, celery and pickles; toss well. Make dressing out of mayonnaise, olive oil, hot sauce, red pepper, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and ketchup. Mix well.
Pour dressing over macaroni and shrimp mixture; mix well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: almost s'mores
directions: Cover crackers with peanut butter.
Place 1 large or several small marshmallows on peanut butter.
Put on plate and place in microwave for 20 seconds.
Take out carefully, they are hot!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut carrots and cook until tender.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise, horseradish and onion.
Top with crumbled crackers mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Cook on High for 6 to 6 1/4 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon oleo or butter.
Cook 1 more minute.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon soda and stir well.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet and cool.
Break in pieces.

title: lasagna
directions: In saucepan, brown beef, onion, garlic and oregano. Add soup, water and vinegar. Simmer 30 minutes. Stir now and then.
In shallow baking dish, arrange 3 alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch flat pan lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts over mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool thoroughly.
Turn over and ice.

title: pistachio cream dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter, sugar and nuts.
Pat in pan and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Add chocolate chips.
Drop by measuring teaspoon on lightly greased sheets (takes 2).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place in oven and quickly turn off heat.
Leave in 5 hours or overnight.
Don't peek.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Trim excess fat from round steak.
Cut into 6 serving-size pieces.
Pound meat with a meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness; set aside.
In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, combine butter, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover and place in microwave oven.
Cook vegetable mixture at High for 4 minutes until carrots are crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, blend cornstarch into the tomato sauce until smooth.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and basil.
Stir into cooked vegetable mixture.
Add meat, turning to coat.
Cover and place in microwave.
Cook meat at Medium for 20 minutes.
Rearrange meat; stir sauce.
Cook at Medium for 20 minutes more until meat is tender.
Serve with hot cooked noodles or mashed potatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
Total cooking time:
44 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook onions in 4 tablespoons oil or Crisco until tender, not brown, then add celery and enough chicken stock to cover (3 or 4 cups).
Cook celery until tender (not mushy), about 10 minutes. Add soy sauce and brown gravy; thicken with flour and water.
Add bean sprouts, etc.
Cook until well heated.
Add chopped chicken. Serve with rice or chow mein noodles and chopped almonds.
Will serve 15 to 20 people.

title: bacon stuffed mushrooms by mom morrison
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and set them aside to use later.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Chop mushroom stems and saute with onion in butter.
When golden, add cream cheese, parsley, lemon pepper seasoning and onion salt. Cook only 1 minute or until cream cheese melts.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture.
Place 1 teaspoon of mixture into each mushroom. Bake mushrooms at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain and discard drippings.
Sprinkle tomato slices, both sides with sugar, salt and flour.
Dip in flour, egg, then flour.
Cook in butter.
Serve with bacon.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix. Let it stand for 24 hours.
Makes a Fix-N-Mix full. Serves 50 people.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over margarine, sugar and salt.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; beat in eggs and add to cooled margarine mixture.
Beat in flour thoroughly, cover and let rise overnight in refrigerator.
Shape and let rise 2 hours before baking at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: aunt helen's asparagus fritters
directions: Drain asparagus.
Mix with eggs and enough bread crumbs to hold mix together.
Drop by ladleful into pan with hot oil.
Fry until lightly browned and drain on absorbent paper.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix together and spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese.
Combine 1/2 stick butter and 1 cup cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: cabbage beef rolls
directions: Wilt cabbage. Cover and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients. Drain leaves and spoon meat mixture in each leaf. Roll up and place in baking dish.

title: sugarless oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together; drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orzo pasta salad
directions: Cook orzo according to package directions.
Drain fruit; reserve 1 3/4 cups juice.
Cook the reserved fruit juice, eggs, sugar and salt to boiling.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Mix with fruit and orzo.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Add Cool Whip.
Makes large salad.

title: sourdough french bread
directions: Dump Starter into the stainless steel mixer bowl.
Add teaspoon of sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 cup water.
Stir.
Take out Starter.

title: cheese ball
directions: Note!
I put the onion and green pepper in blender to chop.

title: chicken in spicy peanut sauce
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of plastic wrap. With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound to 1/4-inch thick.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: mini muffin pizzas
directions: Combine ketchup and mustard.
Spread on muffins.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Put hot dog slices on top.
Garnish with green pepper, olives and onion, if desired.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Then add milk.
Then add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Add lemon extract. Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados to paste with a fork.
Add chopped tomato to avocado paste.
Stir in onion, oregano and lemon juice until thoroughly blended.
Add salt to taste.
Refrigerate sauce, covered, for about 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: denny's house soup
directions: Add all together in saucepan.
Add water until creamy.
Add garlic salt.
Blend together and heat.
Serve with oyster crackers and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut corn off cob; add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoons into frying pan with melted butter or margarine. Brown lightly on both sides.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover top with a layer of chopped pecans.

title: easy caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Combine all but popcorn and cook 9 minutes on High in microwave.
Stir a few times during the nine minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until frothy.
Pour on popped corn and serve.

title: beef rice or texas hash
directions: Brown the hamburg.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Season to taste.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: In a large saucepan
heat
oil	and
butter.
Add mushrooms, onion, celery and garlic; saute 5 minutes.	Add chicken stock; bring to a boil
and
simmer
10 minutes.
Add Tabasco, milk, salt and pepper to
taste.
Blend
flour with cold water and wine (optional).
Stir into soup until smooth and slightly thickened. Sprinkle
with
nutmeg;
add
cream.
Serve
soup sprinkled with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with Marshmallow Creme.
Stir in poppy seed.
It's good with strawberries, peaches, apricots, cake or even chips.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, put lemon or yellow cake mix, instant vanilla pudding, eggs, cooking oil and sour cream.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour 1/2 the batter in.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Put layer of pudding on bottom of dish, then a layer of bananas, then cookies.
Enjoy.

title: veggie squares
directions: Unroll crescent dough on cookie sheet.
Press together seams. Bake 15 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on top of bread.
Finely chop desired vegetables such as green pepper, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, radishes, etc., and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Press on them with hand to push into cheese mixture.
Cut into squares. Chill.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease skillet and bake at 450° until done.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Measure flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon and salt into a bowl. Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients over creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Form into balls. Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies crack on top.

title: chicken in biscuit
directions: Mix the cream cheese and the 2 tablespoons of margarine until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles and firmly press together where perforated.
Put 1/2 cup of meat mixture into rolls.
Pull up corners and twist.
Pinch the 4 edges together.
Brush with margarine and top with crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° on an ungreased pan for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all-bran and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients; do not overmix.
(Could add 1 mashed banana or raisins, walnuts or 1 chopped apple.)
Fill muffin pans that have been sprayed with vegetable spray about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Melt margarine, adding sugar gradually and blend in applesauce to which baking soda has been added.
Stir flour and raisins. Pour in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: Grease 9-inch baking dish.
Layer bread and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over bread and cheese. Let sit overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: dilly steak-a-bobs
directions: Drain
pineapple,
reserving syrup.
Combine with lemon juice, oil,
Worcestershire, sugar, salt and dill weed.
Cook slowly about
5 minutes.
Cool and pour over steak.
Marinate overnight. Spear
with
skewer
and grill for 5 to 8 minutes. Use marinade to baste kabobs.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: real good granola
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in an Osterizer.
Mix until well blended.
Pour this mixture into a large bowl and add remaining ingredients except raisins.
Mix well.
Place on cookie sheets and sprinkle with cinnamon or drizzle honey over top.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, then turn oven down to 150° for 6 to 8 hours.
Add raisins when granola is removed from oven.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar and sugar; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and egg all at once; stir only until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead gently 1/2 minute.
Pat or roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: In a food processor or blender, combine the garlic, salt (if desired) and oil.
Process the ingredients until they are smooth. Add the basil and pine nuts or walnuts and process the ingredients until they are smooth.
(You may need to stop the machine once or twice to scrape the bowl or jar.)
Tip: For thinner sauce, add chicken or vegetable broth.

title: fruit tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: great chipped beef dip(yield: 12 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375°.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Add to milk mixture. Add eggs and flour.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.
Shape into buns.
Let rise until double.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: uncle kevin's applesauce(kids recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; cook until tender.

title: ukranian poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 medium loaf pans.
Heat poppy seed and milk together in a saucepan.
Remove from heat right before it boils.
Let stand until room temperature.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with poppy seed mixture, stirring well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and lemon rind at the end.
Bake in well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put oysters and juice in a pot with 2 cups water; let set for 2 hours in fridge.
Use 2 pots, in first pot melt butter.
Add oysters and liquid.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and cook for 5 minutes.
In second pot, heat milk until hot, not boiling.
Pour milk into oyster pot; heat until very hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: jiffy corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork chop
directions: In bottom of crock-pot place potatoes, then carrots and onions. On top of vegetables place pork chops.
Pour soup over top.
Do not use water.
Cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours.
Suggestions:
Use vegetables and sauce over noodles.

title: apple streusel coffee cake
directions: Put cereal in a bag and crush.
In a bowl combine crushed cereal, flour, cinnamon, brown sugar and melted margarine.
Set aside.

title: crisp kraut salad
directions: Turn kraut into colander and drain, pressing out all liquid. Combine in bowl the kraut, pimentos, onion, celery, carrots and green pepper.
In small bowl mix vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper, then stir until dissolved.
Then pour over vegetable mix.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hamburg - vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in large kettle, stirring to break it up.
Add onion and garlic, cooking until yellowed.
Add remaining vegetables and cook, stirring often for 3 minutes.
If there is much fat in the kettle remove all but 1 Tbsp.
Add boiling water, salt, pepper and 2 beef boullion cubes.
Cover and let simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
During last 10 minutes of cooking time add the canned tomatoes.

title: peggy's layered salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and sugar, set aside. Layer remaining ingredients in order given and top with mayonnaise mixture.

title: refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Bring all of the above to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Place sliced cukes, onions and dill in a non-metal container.
I use a gallon jar and the above is just enough for 1 gallon of pickles.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over sliced cukes and store in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: punch
directions: Stir all ingredients except 7-Up in a large pot.
In punch bowl, pour in 1/2 punch mix and 2 liters of 7-Up. Serve over ice. Makes about 2 gallons (20 to 30 servings).
